description: UPDATE, APRIL 21 2017: Yearly update...as it turns out, Prince himself saw this around 2013/4, and highly approved of it. I found this out because he had personally found it online and linked it to a few of his assistants and employees, one of whom reached out to me over Facebook to thank me for this illustration. I am so, so happy for this, and to have been able to meet all sorts of people through this work. I feel like I've been personally blessed by one of my dearest heroes. UPDATE, APRIL 21 2016: I had no idea this would blow up in popularity so fast! For any licensing requests and full size versions, please contact me here: robotkat@live.com or www.facebook.com/jen.p.crawfor… . Anyone who wants the design on a shirt, print, or the like can visit my Redbubble: www.redbubble.com/people/robot…? Just a bit of a light parody today. Tumblr seems to really like it. Also, I only went with the Purple Rain look because it's so recognizable. He's had so many outfits.

description: I don't care if it's weird art, shitty art, art that I personally hate. An artist needs to make art that's right for them, despite the noise. Make art time personal time and keep working, no matter what. This is not an anti-critique piece. Critique is good. Useful input is useful. It's up to the artist to decide what is and what isn't. It's about blocking out the kind of distraction and negativity that derails the artistic process. What artists need to worry about most is making their art and to not get involved in all the BS. Absorb all the valid feedback and let the rest just bounce off. Happy Christmas. Edit: Thank you for the DD! I'm glad so many people found it to be cheering to them. After getting some feedback, I'd like to elaborate a little bit on some of the thoughts I've had in response. The first is that these people are not necessarily 'bad guys'. They represent forces that often cause an artist to become upset, reactive, wasteful of energy. (I picked the ones I see people becoming the most upset about on DeviantART and on the internet in general. I personally have no problem with people who copy my work, but some people do). The artist is the filter and it is the artist who decides how these people hurt or help their ability to make art. There will always be trolls, haters, critics, copiers, feedback both good and bad, and the artist must always express themselves in spite of this, to take in what is useful to them, let the rest go, and not get caught up in their own negativity. This ideal artist is not at war with a hostile environment but at peace with reality. Secondly, I've made it into a print (as per requested) but am also allowing the full DL of the original drawing for anyone who wants to print it out and just hang it up in their work space as a little reminder.
title: an artist's job is to make art hibbary Watch Cartoons & Comics Traditional Media Comics Other hibbary

description: the little mermaid aprox 45 mins to an hr, nothin too detailed, had to get this done before the day ended. its abit rough but i think it has potential. when u look at the ocean, u see its relentless, its bigger than us and it never stops, wave after wave endlessly changing, its restless.. frantic, turning, loud and scary at times, and grey and shite others, it can be cold or warm, its clear here and murky there, it can look red, green, purple, and black etc...etc.. and every now and then, it can be still, calm, nice, peaceful and beautiful, even though u know its going to change again soon..so all u can do is enjoy the moment, when ur in it. and while it lasts. (sigh..)

description: Peter Pan played a large role in my childhood memories. I always wished I had Tinker Bell so I could fly like him (I love flying and floating things) Sometimes when I laid down and couldn't sleep, I visualized him knocking on the window in the middle of the night and take me to Neverland, stay young forever. Though this story seems to be bright and innocent it's kinda bitter sweet to me. Peter and Wendy loves each other. But Wendy had to return home, grew up, unlike Peter. All the lost boys followed Wendy back to the town, and Peter was left alone in Neverland. The ending always made me cried a little inside. Tools : Watercolor, Photoshop. Thank you for the DD!! means a lot to me XD

description: Here comes a thought, that might alarm you. what they all said and oh how it harmed me; “something you did, it failed to be charming. Something you said, are suddenly swarming” and oh, I’m losing sight, I’m losing touch, all those little things seem to matter so much. that they confuse me. that i might lose me. take a moment to remind yourself to take a moment and find yourself, take a moment and ask yourself, if this is how I fall apart. but i tell myself that its not its not its not its not its not. its okay its okay its okay its okay its okay. I have everything everything everything everything to fear. but im still here, still here, still here edit: Hey, sorry if i gave off the impression that i was back to being like i was last year, haha.. just, this one particular episodes song lyrics struck a nerve in me. strongly. triggering horrid memories.

description: THERE WILL BE SPOILERS IN THIS DESCRIPTION! LOOK AWAY IF YOU HAVEN'T READ "DARKNESS OF DRAGONS"!!! --- Ok, I know a lot of people weren't happy with Peacemaker's origin but...I really couldn't see it going any other way. It was literally the only solution for a gigantic problem, and I am completely ok with it. Yes, like most of you I adored Darkstalker. He was a fantastic villain and a really likable yet despicable character. His problem was that he was literally so OP that no one could kill him, so changing him was really the only thing that could stop him. He was given the choice to redeem himself, but he refused. If he had accepted defeat and changed his ways then maybe we wouldn't have gotten Peacemaker, the polar opposite of the tyrant. But alas, our favourite stubborn ol' villain had to be enchanted into the form of a baby Night/RainWing to prevent him from causing further damage to Pyyrhia. And for what we got, Peacemaker is pretty damn adorable. I know he was described as being a NightWing with rainbow-coloured sparkles instead of white, but I just loved the idea of giving him little RainWing frills because they looked cuter. Peacemaker is destined to live a wholesome, loving life and I wanted his design to reflect that. If you look closely you'll see that I also gave him rainbow eyes. I did, however, keep the white IceWing spikes that I like to give Darkstalker as a reminder of his past. I would also usually draw NightWings with black horns but in this case I thought it looked better to make them white to represent his IceWing heritage.

description: It's finally here as promised - the commemorative picture for my half-ton visits landmark on my page, which happened over a month ago. Ah well, at least it fell near enough to Christmas. What a coinkydink! With nearly 4 times the votes, it was decided that a massive tickle picture of the New Hatchford girls would be the one. However, they did not come alone. Rather, they are tickled by their outgoing counterparts, who we last saw in a Christmas picture two years ago and are making a one-off return. Man, time flies. I matched up the old and new characters depending on how much they have in common with each other, as follows... Lauren and Nadja, getting her navel and midriff tickled by the former, are both exotic curvy girls who share tastes in dancing (belly dancing particularly), socialising and dating many men. Robi is tickling a hogtied Folami's feet. Both are outspoken, love hip-hop, have a sense of pride for their hometown and even speak in street dialect regularly. Like Folami and Nadja, Robi and Lauren are best mates. Kitty Marie is pretty much the prototype of Ingrid, or directly influenced her creation, because they share so much in common. They are blue-eyed brunette musicians who are middle-class and trendy, wear striped tops and dislike their feet getting touched. No wonder why Ingrid's face is that of panic and ticklish laughter as Kitty lightly strokes those big feet of hers. Ana-Lea brought her black labrador (or as she lovingly calls him - "that stinky dog") to lick away the grease off the soles of her shy Irish counterpart Mairead. Both are perpetually barefoot, auburn-haired and have very sensitive skin. Bey is relentlessly working over the vulnerable armpits of a bound Darlene - a fellow blonde who debuted before everyone else in the cast like Bey before her and is/was a favourite with the fans during their tenure. The Chimpette is in the back getting her feet licked in stocks by a baby reindeer (because Christmas) as the Chimp happily looks on unconvincingly in a Santa suit (because Christmas). If you don't know why there were matched here, you're probably new... I hope you all enjoy this picture card, and thank you once again for you continued patronage! All characters here belong to

description: So followers of my blog at amburgered.tumblr.com will know that I've been drawing this little Sheldon comic/doodle page thing for a while. But for those who don't know him, Meet Sheldon! The tiny dinosaur that thinks he's a turtle. He wears an acorn on his back in lieu of a shell. I've decided to start posting him here as well, but also offering prints! As I've never used the dA print system before, this is more of a test of how it works. If it seems to be working, I'll post the rest of Sheldon's escapades as well!

description: Look here, another wave of Munnen passing by. As usual they are busy being busy but some interactions are clearly notable when looking a little closer. Loads of chatting and laughter here but also there are some of them whose mind seems troubled. some escape their daily routine and try to face the current but overall the atmosphere is pretty at ease. Except of course the one to whom the attention is drawn at first glance! Seems that she is searching for something. But look at her face, something good is appearing at the horizon. Might very well be hope! Did she find what she was looking for? (2012) FaceBook

description: I needed to do a thing for myself, and made a magpie dragon. BUY THIS PRINT AND MORE ON MY ETSY SHOP; Interested in a commission? View my pricelist here; A commission is a piece of art that you request an artist to make in exchange for payment. This can be anything from pet portraits, creature concepts, youtube thumbnails, original characters, comic covers,...anything at all! Here are some examples I have done recently. You can see more of my artwork on my Etsy Shop as well as in the Deviantart Gallery. Ordering commissions from me just just one of the many ways you can show your support and keep this youtube channel and my business going. It also helps with living expenses and convention trips. You can also purchase ready made art prints from the Etsy Shop, and the Ebay Shop. You can also become a Patron on my Patreon page and win exclusive rewards including video topic suggestions, convention exclusive items and more! Etsy Shop; www.etsy.com/uk/shop/MadMunchk… Ebay Shop; www.ebay.co.uk/usr/mad-munchki… Patreon; www.patreon.com/madmunchkin Of course, continuously watching the youtube channel, ( liking and commenting on my videos and following my content on other websites is also support in itself. Remember to also follow the Mad Munchkin Facebook page and the Deviant Art Gallery to stay up to date and informed on how I have been doing and what I plan on doing in the future. Please note that I run a first come first serve policy. If you wish to have your commission done for a certain date, an additional Â£20 must be paid along with the deposit of the commission. This will push your commission to the top of the list to ensure your commission is completed in time. Please allow at least 14 days for the commission to be done. Remember if your commission is not a priority order the time that it will take to be completed will vary due to commitments, convention trips and video schedules. Please note I will not draw anything that would not be considered Safe for Work. In other words I will not draw any content that is not PG13 suitable. This includes drug abuse, Alcohol abuse, sexual content including nudity, and extreme violence and gore. If the subject of a drawing goes against my morals, religious or political beliefs I will negotiate with the client and come to some sort of compromise. For more details on what I will and will not draw please click this link for the full terms and conditions document; docs.google.com/document/d/10w… My Prices are in British Pound Sterling, though I do take foreign currency. You can use an online currency converter to see how much your commission order will cost in your currency. When placing an order for a commission I ask for customers to pay an upfront deposit of 50% of the total cost of their commission order. This deposit is non refundable so please ensure that when you place your order you are able to pay the rest of the cost of the commission when the commission is completed. I take all payments via paypal. Please remember than if you post the commission online to credit me as the original artist so I get credit, exposure and further custom. If you are interested in ordering a commision, please send an email with full details of your commission order to; amy.methven.art@hotmail.co.uk. Thank you for the ongoing support and I look forward to hearing from you. Thanks for watching! I’m Mad Munchkin. Stay Creative.

description: I spied a 50p on my desk so decided to draw Britannia that was on the tails side. I'm not that patriotic, but I do love the the immagery and sence of identity we have when it comes to stuff like this. And I do like being British. Or mainly living in Britain. I like that there is history and culture and a good story wherever I go and all the quirks and eccentricities that come with it. And I would always procliam myself British first. Never Welsh. Despite being born and raised in Wales I ('ve been made to) feel like I don't belong. But that doesn't matter. There's more than enough to keep me entertained here. Anyway, yay for our little island and all its stuff.

description: Lapis Lazuli from Steven Universe, depicted as the goddess of numismatics Based on one of the ivory-carved panels on the precious coin cabinet of Elector Maximilian I of Bavaria. This cabinet for ancient gold coins was made of ivory, wood and lapis lazuli. I've been to Munich in summer and visited the National Museum where the cabinet is displayed. Drawing process available at youtu.be/MUHc8Y8x0Xc Tools I used: pencil, M&G gel pen and Kuretake Gansai Tambi watercolor. description: Pfffft... what's with all that "she's gotta be sweet, he's gotta be kind" crap. I need none of that! THIS is the real list. A couple of weeks ago I saw this stupid stupid stupid Sandra Bullock movie, the one where she and Nicole Kidman are witches. Well, her character, as a child, casts a spell describing the perfect man, and she makes him impossible so she'd never fall in love. So... vaguely inspired by that, I decided to do my own list And I decided to do both boy AND girl, so as to cover any chance I'm sorry if it's huge, it wouldnt have worked the same way had I posted it in two pieces. Just scroll, you lazy bastard. Oh, and full view is not recommended, it's MANDATORY Comments are more than welcome, I just don't expect much critique on the artwork since it's only for fun. Oh, and before you comment, please remember, it's HUMOR.

description: This was a commission from the father of A Real American Hero himself, Ron Rudat. He was the creative genius at Hasbro in the 80's who designed the majority of the characters we know and love from the GI Joe line such as Snake-Eyes, Storm Shadow, Scarlet, The Baroness etc. so it was a real honour (and a bit intimidating) to have him ask for these characters (and himself) in my style. I think he's going to have this image printed so that he can use it for autographs at the various GI Joe conventions in the upcoming months. For the story behind the pic, you need to watch the documentary that Ron and his son are making about the original team of designers who created the line-up of Joes in the 80's called Operation: Blast Off.

description: Yep... this was my first daydream doodle of Flapjack... And then I painted it (acrylics)... and then I pitched it at cartoon network. And then as I developed it for a couple of years, I realized that Flapjack needs someone to interact with. Who would bring out more of his personality (and so he didn't have to talk to himself). So I gave him K'nuckles. And it got too dark. Because K'nuckles is a rapscallion. So I gave him comfort and safety (Bubbie). And changed her to a real whale. Initially she was a little more of a stick-in-the-mud like Davie from Davie and Goliath. But then when I was auditioning voices I found Roz Ryan(who does Bubbie's voice) and everything got a million times better... copyright 2001

description: [EDIT] ok, ok after 500 favs and an artbook publication I won't scrap it, don't worry And thank you for the feedback!!! ^^ ...I wanted to name it "Ich tanze in meinem Kopf", but I was not sure if it would sound well ^^' <strike>Sooo.... although it is just a DOODLE (no crits, thx, I'm going to scrap it anyway), I have to explain this and that to you...</strike> This picture has been stuck in my head for over two weeks, I tried to draw it 3 or 4 times... And the story behind it is as follows:- my car has been broken for several weeks - and thus I was forced to go to school by bus. As it usually takes about an hour to get there, I took my mp4 player with me... I adore that feeling, when I can imagine that I sing and dance, free - even in the biggest crowd! So I kept daydreaming, when I suddenly noticed that the bus was literally full of ppl listening to their own players! Just a few were talking, the rest sat silently, with their eyes nearly closed and their earphones on. And that was the moment when I thought that possibly all of them were dancing and singing in their heads... Anyway, that was kind of a sad view, to be honest ;_;

description: 11/29/08: You guys are so awesome xD. over 1,800 faves! Ridiculous o_o. Ridiculously awesome, that is! Anyway, thanks everyone <3. 11/22/07: .....1000 faves....omg o_o. THANK YOU EVERYONE. I can't believe it...:'D EDIT4 9/29/07: Over 900 faves O___O -shocked- Ya'll are the best eeee !! And I'm uploading a newer version with even more watermarks due to more people trying to sell it. ....please, guys, DON'T steal and sell! EDIT3 8/7/07: Wow.....800+ faves OMG XD. I'm so, so happy that you guys like this picture so much. Thank you all!!! EDIT2 8/12/06: Almost a year later, and 300+ favs! Thank you all so, so much!! Unfortunetely, after an incident with an art thief who was selling this picture...., I have decided to watermark it. I really didn't want to have to, since I find that watermarks that do their job well usually wreck the presentation of the image completely. I'm going with minimal watermarking--I placed my little mini dragon watermarks on all four phoenixes as well as a text one, so hopefully that will be enough. If not....I guess I might have to watermark across the phoenixes. So, PLEASE, guys, don't give me a reason to have to do that. DO NOT steal this picture. It is NOT yours; you did not spend hours making it. And, guys, this should really go without saying, but apparentely some people have to be told: definitely do NOT sell my art without my permission. Anyway, thank you all for 300+ favs and enjoy the four phoenixes of the elements ^___^! Available as my first ever Print! The complete "Phoenix of the Elements" series! All the birds here are phoenixes, as in the Phoenix or Firebird, the fantasy bird who can burn itself into ashes at the end of its life and be born anew. Thinking about that bird, I thought, why not make a phoenix who is reborn from water (the Ice Phoenix), or never dies (the Earth Phoenix), or dissapears with the weather (the Air Phoenix)? And that's where this series came about from. I made up all the phoenixes, except the fire one, of course. The traditional phoenix is usually described as being a swan-sized bird with scarlet and gold feathers (sometimes the feathers are sapphire colored) and a brilliant crest. All of my phoenixes have necks more like real birds instead of swans because, let's face it, they might not fit into the picture otherwise XD. Here's information on all 4 of them (I made up all this info, by the way ): The firey Phoenix of the Volcanoes and Fire is in the top left. This is the well-known phoenix of fire, also called the Firebird. He is commander over all that is flame. When his busy, hot-headed life is over, he soars into a volcano. When the volcano erupts, his ashes reform themselves into a new phoenix. Fire can always be reborn, as all that's needed is a little spark from nature or humans. This one here has just been reborn and shows off his majestic beauty in front of his "pyre." The cold Phoenix of the Ice Caves and Ice/Water is in the top right. An ice phoenix is a brother of the well-known fire phoenix. It is very similar to it's brother, the exceptions being how it is reborn and it's coloring, which consists of vivid blues and whites. When it is time for an ice phoenix to be reborn, it builds itself a pyre and sets itself alight. Instead of turning into ashes, however, an ice phoenix will melt like an icecube would and turns into a puddle of frigid water. Within the hour, a new chick emerges from the water. You'll know when it's about to come because the water freezes solid, and then the chick bursts free. The aware Phoenix of the Earth and Ground is in the bottom right. The phoenix of the earth is a creature who has been called by many names over the years: Mother Earth, Nature, and others. He creates mountains with the beats of his wings, ridges by scraping his talons against the soil, and flat deserts with his tail feathers. The Earth Phoenix is unlike other phoenixes in that he does not reincarnate. When he dies, there will be no place to live, and therefore no rebirth. We must help to take care of him and his earth. Lastly, the fabulous Phoenix of the Skies and Weather is in the bottom left. The Phoenix of the Skies, also known as the Air Phoenix, is a truly important bird. She is in charge of of all things related to the sky, such as light, dark, clouds, weather, stars, and the colors of the world. Pretty important job, don't you think? She shares an almost ying-yang connection with the Phoenix of the Earth. Unlike the Earth phoenix, however, and more like the Ice and Fire, she can become reborn. At the end of her life, she fades into mist and cries. The tears fall down to the earth as rain and the mist makes up the storm clouds until, finally, she returns to her solid state, a brand new bird. Her joy is expressed in a beautiful show of colors: a rainbow. And then she resumes her job over all things in heaven's domain. I'm so happy to be finished. Here you can see that all along (from picture 2 onward) I was planning for this print. I made them facing each other in alternating poses and there are many similarities among them. (For example, the fire and ice both have their wings folded and are in side views. The earth and air both are in 3/4ths view and their wings are spread. Other similarities exist .) Thanks for looking and please do comment! If you would like to buy a print, go ahead . All these pictures are Â© to me, "Kalico" Kat, 2005. Do not redistribute or use without my permission (just note me or tell me--most likely I'd say yes! I'd just much rather know ).

description: And now for something COMPLETELY different... I'm glad I finally got that out of my system. The idea for this dates from a few months back, and I had uploaded a study for it [link] . The monster's changed a bit since then though. I'm happy with how it turned out, I suppose it's not that different from what I imagined. I have to give extra credit to ~jusdecrabe who monitored me on MSN while I was doing it, haha. His criticism made it better. Thanks Franks! (This is actually a vexel, but the vexel category is just... so limited. There's no cartoon or illustration subcategory in it. Admins, hear my plea!) That child is in for a BIG SCARE! -- Photoshop CS2 [EDIT] Woahhhh? What a nice surprise I got this morning---a DD! Thanks a lot ^misskittyoooo, and all of you for the nice comments and favs!

description: Due to popular request, I'm uploading a print version of the lovely toe monster, and deleting the old version! "....Ever since I was a little girl, I was terrified of toe monsters. Ever since I read about them in a "Goosebumps" story, I couldn't sleep with my toes hanging out of the blanket. I am now 24 years old, and I still can't fall asleep unless my toes are covered. Until today, The only one who knew about my fear was my fiance, but now, after I have managed to capture the evil beast, I am brave enough to reveal the evil TOE MONSTER that lurks in our bedroom at night...."

description: Sooo... 2000 Watchers! When he saw it, my brother annoyed me saying "Draw a special pictures! Draw a special pictures!", so I wanted to draw something with a lot of characters (like TD, Kids next door, teen titans, my little pony, adventure time, littlest pet shop -all in some kid style- playing a soccer game), but...I didn't have so much time, and I opted for something with my dear 22+2 original TD campers. And that weird girl in the background...it's me... I just wanted to thank you all for watching, comment, and cheer me up when my pets die! I love you people! But please, don't write me in SMS slang, I don't understand it! (Like "sowwie", "plz", "WTF" and so on... seriously, sometimes I spend all my free time trying to understand what they mean!)

description: so, yet another trade cover with romano. these are super fun to do, and are always good to do for a break on the comic pages, since i can paint them and pretty much do whatever i like. i am so very happy to know i have 3 more of these suckers to do in the coming month, that i can go to whenever i feel i need a break. started this one last night to get a small break from pages, i just felt like painting. was only going to work on it for a little while, but it seemed to go really fast and i seemed to get ALOT done on it before i would usually stop working (due to the large faces and one bust which goes rather quickly for me to paint) so i decided to finish it. i had already done 3 pages when i started this, and then worked on this for 6 hours straight. i cannot believe how bad my hand hurt at the end of the night. fully rendering these things always takes it's toll on my hands, where coloring pages doesn't really do much to them. hmm..... initial lines by romano molenaar, digital paints by me, nei ruffino. feel free to comment but know i have discouraged criticism as this piece is finished and i do not plan on working it any further..

description: Here's the first of a series of images I'll be doing based on a crazy idea I had. Wendy's is the only fast food chain I know of that has a female mascot. So I thought about doing some sexy, sleepy/DiD parody images with the mascots of other major fast food brands defeating and capturing her. I do love to eat at Wendy's and I've always liked the look of their girl-next-door mascot. The first one is KFC's Colonel Sanders. The dialogue just came to me when I was doing the image. The pose was inspired by a vampire anime/manga series I saw on another site (can't remember the name though). This pic has Premium Content available. The high-res file (16x21") of this and a TOPLESS version (no bra, bare shoulders) are both available as a premium item bundle for just 50 DA points (or around 50 CENTS I think). It's also available to my patrons on Patreon (www.patreon.com/cuttlesquidsle…)

description: No page this week, let's let Sarah sleep it off. But! I am gonna try and pull together some GND merch on Society6 or the like, in time for Christmas pressies. In a carefully-dancing-around-depictions-of-copyrighted-characters way, and trying to be very specific to the comic itself. This is me testing the waters. All* of the wee pics were re-drawn in high quality, and could be reassembled or used alone. Faves? Things you feel are missing? too much Fluffy Owl? Needs moar - what? Would you be interested in purchasing this picture if I uploaded it poster-quality here on devart? t-shirts, magnets, what? Do you buy stuff on devart, or another preferred online art buying platform? Is this tacky panhandling or are you genuinely interested in GND goodies? Can I guilt any of y'all to toss a coupla bucks my way after nigh on 8 years of comic? I'm putting this as print-purchasable, but I am not locking it from download, so, whevs. But please share your thoughts/criticisms/wishlists. (* OK, the "messaj" panel was last-minute addition and actual recycling; would be redrawn. Or another goblin moment?)

description: Tino (APH Finland) and Carl Gustav Emil Mannerheim, the Marshall of Finland. as recommended by Tiriol whose dA was deactivated but you may remember him as Germany featuring in many cosplay videos in www.youtube.com/user/Rintamasu… Coloring process available at youtu.be/-t1k-0ikaw4 Mannerheim's uniform is based on the one in this photo d3ncwv2e9zpfbf.cloudfront.net/… Tino's uniform is the M/36. Thank you, Tiriol for having help me with the designs, colors and material of the uniforms ( I get to wear that coat Finland is wearing ) Finland and Mannerheim was recommended to me two years ago, but I've waited till this momentous occasion to put the idea to paper Nope! Just kidding. I was procrastinating and being uninspired by the lack of sunlight. I made around 3-4 sketches with different idea, Mannerheim reading, Mannerheim riding horse, etc and I realized I can't draw horses Then it struck me 2 days ago that Finland's 100th birthday will be on December 6 and I have not dome anything. I rushed too make the final sketch. I tried to illustrated Mannerheim to resemble how he is in real life as much as possible (avoiding turning him to a Dr. Phil look-alike as with the case of Otto von Bismarck hanakoofthejungle.deviantart.c…) I started doing line art only at 2 a.m on 6 December and finished coloring around 8. Some processes can be found on my tumblr (hanakoofthejungle.tumblr.com/) I am pleased that the drawing was finally completed on Finland's Centennial of Independence And Happy Independence Day to all my Finnish fellow deviants Tools: pencil, M&G gel pen and Kuretake Gansai Tambi watercolor. Youtube: www.youtube.com/user/Hanako649 Tumblr: hanakoofthejungle.tumblr.com/ Facebook: www.facebook.com/Hanakooftheju… Instagram: www.instagram.com/hanakoofthej…

description: Okay, first and foremost, I adore the Wings of Fire books. I am here to discuss a massive problem I have with the fandom. --- One thing that myself and many other dragon artists have noticed, is the massive surge in comments comparing our work to Wings of Fire. Yes, a few of us have drawn WOF fan art and that is sure to draw in the WOF community, but it's when we get comments like that on our drawings of our original characters who look absolutely nothing like anything from the WOF universe that really pisses us off. Yes, I used to experience something similar when I still drew Warriors and Cats, but let me explain: Warriors is set in a universe very similar to our own (just with feral cats able to form a complex political hierarchy), so any original cat artwork with normal-looking cats set in a pleasant European-looking forest is bound to be compared to Warriors, because there are very few surface differences. Wings of Fire, on the other hand, takes place in a highly-developed fantasy universe, with very distinct styles for the dragon species (so far as having drawings of what each species looks like at the beginning of the books), and having very detailed descriptions of the dragon societies and cultures. Wings of Fire is VERY unique and easy to recognise. This is why it is so insulting to us dragon artists when you say "this looks like Wings of Fire". 99% of us have our own original stories with our own unique ways of drawing dragons (almost all of which bear no resemblance to the Wings of Fire dragons). You aren't paying any attention to what we draw other than the fact that there are dragons in it. This is incredibly shallow and completely disregards all the hard work that myself and other dragon artists put into our character designs and stories. I mean, I even received a comment on my Spyro Hero MAP saying "this looks like Wings of Fire". WHAT?! Spyro and Wings of Fire and the most polar opposites in terms of tone and style! Not to mention Spyro came out 13 years before the first Wings of Fire book was published! The only thing they share in common is, of course, there are dragons in them. To all younger WOF fans, PLEASE DO NOT DO THIS TO ANYONE! It is incredibly insulting and honestly it makes me want to stop making Wings of Fire art.

description: Well after like, 2 years of dilly dallying and putting this off, ive FINALLY generated a defenite character design of my character Eclipse! For those of you who dont remember (which no doubt would be most of you), Eclipse is my own personal superhero. His real name is Deacon Ford, a clinically depressed student in New York, attending an art college. He has the ability of shadowmancy, the ability to create, manipulate, and turn shadows into tangible objects. In reality, shadows are not the abscence of light, they are in fact dark energy, a form of matter that scientists have not discovered. Light displaces the dark energy and causes it to move, as if you were to place an object in a bucket of water, the water would just be displaced. Eclipse has the ability to see in the dark, as well as bend shadows to his will. Anyway, Ill post more of his backstory later on. For now, enjoy the drawing! ^^ Used ~Falln-Brushes's smoke brushes for the smoke effect.

description: EDIT: YAY published in EQD www.equestriadaily.com/2012/10… This comic strip is loosely based on the scene from Episode 17 Season one of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic - Stare Master - where Fluttershy forces her chickens back into their coop using the force of her stare. I've kinda extrapolated that into a Hypnotoad-meets-Jedi-Mind-Trick thing. The last frame is the punch-line. She's trying to get you to recommend this to a fan site. A homage of sorts to Hypnotoad Some of this comic is drawn from scratch in Photoshop using a mixture of brushes, layers and vectors. Other components have other sources, which I have favorited and linked to below. The ponies are based on images generated using General Zoi's pony Flash tool: (generalzoi.deviantart.com/#/d4…, with some modification. I re-drew Fluttershy's eyes using a combination of Brushes and Vectors, using this tutorial as a guide (mlp-vectorclub.deviantart.com/…. Yes, I do realize that there is a layering error, I tried to upload a fixed version, but it's still using the old one for some reason. Frame 1 The background in Frame 1 is Matty 4z's MLP Garden Path (perfectblue97.deviantart.com/f…. The chickens, chicken coop, fence etc were scratch built using a combination of brushes and vectors (except for the eyes, which are just shrunken down pony eyes from General Zoi's pony creator). Fluttershy's Cutie Mark was created by Grendo11: (grendo11.deviantart.com/galler…. As was Twilight Sparkle's Cutie Mark: (grendo11.deviantart.com/art/Tw…. Frame 2 The background is scratch built. I couldn't find a good image of Gilda from the series that I likes, so I created a posable Gilda using a combination of vectors, brushes and Photoshop layers. I used these images to get the look right, Sulyo's Roaring Gilda: (sulyo.deviantart.com/art/Gilda…, PeachSpice's Gilda Vector: (peachspices.deviantart.com/art…, and Elsdrake's Hippogriff Gilda: (elsdrake.deviantart.com/art/Hi…. The head in frame 4 was entirely drawn by Sulyo: (sulyo.deviantart.com/art/Gilda…, and is used here with their kind permission. As I couldn't draw one nearly good enough. The eye was also Created by General Zoi's pony Flash tool: (generalzoi.deviantart.com/#/d4… for expediencyconsistency. I previously used this image in Fluttershy's Secret. Frame 3 The background Is Rarity's Room by Mandy Dax (perfectblue97.deviantart.com/f…. Sweetie Belle was created using General Zoi's pony creator, but was modified as I couldn't get the pose right in the pony creator. It was inspired by this image (moongazeponies.deviantart.com/…. Rarity's Cutie mark is from UP1TER (up1ter.deviantart.com/gallery/… Frame 4 I've basically used parts from the other frames here. Nothing much new. To see this in its full resolution, please download.

description: I thought I'd try my hand at making comics, and what other way to do it than in the style of The Loud House. The main purpose of this art piece is rather interesting. When I look back at some of the fanfictions I wrote, I realized that only two of them ("Certificate of Excellence" and "Shut the Duck Up") seemed to have the type of humor that replicates the actual show, as all my other fanfictions have some form of drama to them, and would usually depict thing you'd never see in the show (violent assaults, massive hate crowds, real-life songs). I made this comic to see if I can create something Loud House related that actually has the type of humor the show has. As such, I examined some images of the Loud House graphic novels online to see what the humor is like, and tried to brainstorm some ideas, and this was one of them. I actually have a few more in mind, and would release them soon. Also, I thought it'd be fun if I nicknamed my comics like the names of the graphic novels. I thought "My Own Little Chaos" was perfect, since it's a fanmade project, and it makes it look like I'm throwing in my two cents for an upcoming product. Real fact: It took me two days to make this whole comic. The hardest part was outlining it. I guess it's true that that more detail there is in a drawing, the harder it is.

description: Something big is returning in 2018 So yeah, I was chatting with my friends and the topic of Spyro's Got Talent came up. I mentioned how I have tried to revive the show several times in the past, and we all started pitching ideas of how the show could be revived for Spyro's 20th Anniversary (because hey, if Activision won't do anything special, someone might as well try). A bunch of ideas were thrown around and they were all hilarious and awesome, so I have planned to make one final episode (more like a mini-movie) for 2018 to celebrate our favourite purple dragon and his friends as they compete to win 10,000 gems in Avalar's most loved Talent Show!

description: So, it's finally here. Let's start these summer months and my freedom from mandatory higher education the right way, shall we? This is the first picture I've officially released here using my new laptop, graphics tablet and Clip Studio Paint (though I still use Paint Tool SAI and Paint Shop Pro because old habits never die and all that), and it coincides with this being my 400th deviation here, as well as having 2000 watchers of my page (or near enough - who's really counting accurately). Also, it's the first time that most of this new cast have been tickled for the first time, such is the way that newcomers to my art world have to be initiated. Usually my pictures aren't that massive, but with new tech I can at the very least post some higher resolution images in the future. I've started to use the watercolour tool along with airbrush - especially with the hair, as it's much neater and easier to do. Anyway, thanks for being there, being patient and giving the support that helps my motivation to do these things... when I have the time. Also, out of the six ladies tickled here, who has the most ticklish feet out of all of them? You won't win anything for guessing right, except basking in your out rightness, maybe... description: Please note, this comic was originally intended to be 10-15 pages long. The lack of lead up and detailed explanation on this page reflects the fact that the comic was supposed to be a lot shorted and simpler than it ended up being. EDIT: I've had a some people react quite badly to this comic. Some even found it a little distressing that I've taken Twilight's horn away (Wounded veterans have been been mentioned in the comments). When I first wrote this comic, my vision was that this was an academic exercise set by Celestia to help Twilight to better relate to other ponies, as well as to better understand herself. So I've updated the text to clearly state that this fact. I've also tidied up the page a little. Still the original vectors, though. This edit means that some of the following pages might sound a little odd. Original Description I know that it doesn't look much, but this is my most ambitious Pony comic to date. I've tried to use as many original components as I can (Inkscape and Photoshop), but you might recognize some old favorites from other (more talented) authors. This comic was inspired by the episode Winter Wrap-Up, where Twilight tries to get by without using her Magic, but in the end she uses it even though she isn't supposed to. Princess Celestia sent Twilight to Ponyville in order to get to know other ponies, and to discover life outside of her books and magic, but in most episodes she seems to solve problems using books and magic. Twilight solved three simple problems with magic, that any Earth Pony could have solved using their hooves. She used her magic instinctively. Princess Celestia wants her to find a way to do things without using magic, and to see things from other pony's perspectives. She's not being cruel (and this is supposed to be the "real" Celestia). She's trying to help Twilight to explore the other things that make Twilight Sparkle who she is. Anything that isn't directly attributed to somebody is either based on an image from the show's advertizing material for the show, or is scratch drawn (Some things are a combination of the two). I didn't use General Zoi's Pony Creator for any of this (yay). As you can see from the “Cyclops” pony in frame 7, I'm still getting to grips with Inkscape, and Ponies in general. Twilight Sparkle's Cutie Mark is by Grendo11 (grendo11.deviantart.com/art/Tw…) Part 2: perfectblue97.deviantart.com/a… (Updated version) Part 3: perfectblue97.deviantart.com/a… Part 4: perfectblue97.deviantart.com/a… Part 5: perfectblue97.deviantart.com/a… Part 6: perfectblue97.deviantart.com/a… Part 7: perfectblue97.deviantart.com/a… Frame 1, Scootaloo's expression is based on this image (bobthelurker.deviantart.com/ar…). Frame 3 and 4: Background (gameguy001.deviantart.com/art/…). Frame 5: Rainbow Dash is Angry Rainbow Dash by 90Sigma (90sigma.deviantart.com/art/Ang…). Derpy's Cutie Mark is by Ooklah (ooklah.deviantart.com/art/Cuti…). Frame 6: The background is from the show itself. Frame 7: Background is Library Upper Floors (Twilight's Bedroom) by DaringDashie (daringdashie.deviantart.com/ar…). Frame 8: Sorry, I'm being really lazy here. This is from the show itself. I wonder how Celestia is writing that letter without using her magic (no glow?). Frame 9: This one is based on a couple of different images. Including Veggie55's Rainy Days (veggie55.deviantart.com/art/Ra…) and Library Upper Floors (Twilight's Bedroom) by DairingDashie (daringdashie.deviantart.com/ar…). I used them both as a base. One for the window and the other for the curtain, along with some tweaks. Also based on the original image from the show. Frame 10 and 11: Same as above. Frame 12: Same as Frame 8. Frame 13 and 14: Same as Frame 9.

description: Hehe, just a cute image that popped into my head last night so I started doodling it to keep myself active. Just finished a pretty long livestream colouring this, but it was fun~ The context I imagine for this picture: Spirit was just hesitantly trying to make some little joke, a rather flirtatious one, so he was sure it would either go over completely the wrong way or just end up being really awkward. Best case scenario, she found it funny. But surprisingly, not only did it actually WORK on her but was far more effective than Spirit Wind could have imagined, as the very next moment he's blinded by a wall of feathers Hehe I just love how this came out. it was a cute and funny little idea and was fun to draw. Good practice too and some awkward posing there to work with. Just came off a long live stream on Picarto doing this, so a big thanks to everypony who watched!! Oh, and in case it isn't pretty obvious by now by all the subtle little hints like pictures and small cameo's of derpy in the background of pretty much any picture featuring Spirit Wind here, I like Derpaderp quite a damm lot. pretty much about the same as I love Pinkie Pie at this point X3 she's so loveable and endearing and adorable. And I know this sounds really dumb and typical so judge me if you will but I think she and Spirit make an adorable couple >w< Background: Sorry I altered the colours of the tree slightly to match the ones I was using Please visit my Patreon for more art and special rewards!

description: "Someday, I'll get out of here! There will be no walls to hold me! You'll see. I'll live the most wonderful adventures a dog could ever dream of having!" "But don't you like it here? With mama and papa?" "I do, Theo. But I think life can be so much more!" --- More of Steban and his little brother, Theo I don't know why, but I really like drawing these two together. Steban, Theo and their older brothers, Mitchel and Darren were all homeschooled. Their father, Eric, was overprotective and rarely ever let them go out of the house. This only made Steban's thirst for adventure grow, together with his urge to leave home. Steban never really realized the value of his family and his old life until he was too far to turn back Oh, and Eric was the owner of a library. That's why their house is full of books! I was listening to this song while drawing this: [link] pay attention to the lyrics I just love them so much! And it has a lot to do with Steban! --- Today is meh berthdaaaay omg THANK YOU ALL SO MUCH FOR THE HAPPY BIRTHDAY WISHES!!!! you people are AWESOME!!!!!!

Check it out, at long last I'm making a new print available on DeviantArt... AND IT'S IN COLOR!!! (and that's a big deal because this only, like, the 2nd time either of my Dead Days characters have ever been in color... it was a shock to me too!) What better print to hoist up than the frontman to the "popular band" The Flaming Poosters striking onna those "too-coo-fo-schoo" brit-band poses!! Oooh! Hot Crap! So if you like the print and wanna support a starving cartoonist order yours today! By the way, you can also enter to win THE ORIGINAL ART for this piece [link] as well as a slick DEAD DAYS BOOK by entering my DEAD DAYS RAFFLE! Go here [link] for details, but HURRY! You only have like a day and a half left to signup! Alright, that's it for me. I'm exhausted. See you when I post the raffle winners! Later! -John P.S. Buy the print. description: Coloured Sketch commission of two siblings based on :iconKenisu=of-Dragons character concepts. A commission is a piece of art that you request an artist to make in exchange for payment. Click the thumbnail to see my full price list of commissioned work. This can be anything from pet portraits, creature concepts, youtube thumbnails, original characters, comic covers,...anything at all! Ordering commissions from me just just one of the many ways you can show your support and keep this youtube channel and my business going. It also helps with living expenses and convention trips. You can also purchase ready made art prints from the Etsy Shop, and the Ebay Shop. You can also become a Patron on my Patreon page and win exclusive rewards including video topic suggestions, convention exclusive items and more! Etsy Shop; www.etsy.com/uk/shop/MadMunchk… Ebay Shop; www.ebay.co.uk/usr/mad-munchki… Patreon; www.patreon.com/madmunchkin Of course, continuously watching the youtube channel, ( liking and commenting on my videos and following my content on other websites is also support in itself. Remember to also follow the Mad Munchkin Facebook page and the Deviant Art Gallery to stay up to date and informed on how I have been doing and what I plan on doing in the future. If you are interested in ordering a commission here are the options available to you; At the moment there are three options available to you; 1; Sketch Starting from just Â£30, a sketch is a black and white piece with a plain background, perfect for more simple concepts or studies for you to further develop or colour for yourself later. Of Additional characters and props cost just Â£20 extra. 2; Coloured Sketch Starting from just Â£50, a coloured sketch is a coloured illustration of a character on a plain background. Perfect for using as PNGs to use on your own background or youtube thumbnail. Additional characters and props cost just Â£25 extra. 3; Full Coloured piece Starting from just Â£200, full coloured piece is a fully shaded rendered and coloured piece of art with a background and one character. Perfect for comic or book covers or youtube thumbnails. Extra characters and props are Â£100 extra. 4; Youtube Thumbnail A brand new item for 2018! Starting at Â£100, a youtube thumbnail is exactly what it says on the tin. Similar to a full coloured piece though with a simpler finish these are perfect for making your youtube videos stand out! Additional characters cost just Â£50 extra. 5; Convention Badge A brand new item for 2018! Starting from just Â£40, a convention badge is perfect for wearing while at conventions to let people know who you are! By wearing your OC on your lanyard (not indluced with the badge) you will stand out from the crowd! TERMS AND CONDITIONS Please note that I run a first come first serve policy. If you wish to have your commission done for a certain date, an additional Â£20 must be paid along with the deposit of the commission. This will push your commission to the top of the list to ensure your commission is completed in time. Please allow at least 14 days for the commission to be done. Remember if your commission is not a priority order the time that it will take to be completed will vary due to commitments, convention trips and video schedules. What I will draw; PG suitable content Humans Animals/ pets Original Characters Fan Art What I will NOT draw Blood and Gore Sexual content Drug use or alcohol abuse My OCs with any OCs. (sorry) Please note I will not draw anything that would not be considered Safe for Work. In other words I will not draw any content that is not PG13 suitable. This includes drug abuse, Alcohol abuse, sexual content including nudity, and extreme violence and gore. If the subject of a drawing goes against my morals, religious or political beliefs I will negotiate with the client and come to some sort of compromise. PRICES AND HOW TO PAY My Prices are in British Pound Sterling, though I do take foreign currency. You can use an online currency converter to see how much your commission order will cost in your currency. When placing an order for a commission I ask for customers to pay an upfront deposit of 50% of the total cost of their commission order. This deposit is non refundable so please ensure that when you place your order you are able to pay the rest of the cost of the commission when the commission is completed. I take all payments via paypal. Please remember than if you post the commission online to credit me as the original artist so I get credit, exposure and further custom. If you are interested in ordering a commision, please send me a private note here on deviantart, tweet me on twitter, pm me on facebook or send an email with full details of your commission order to; amy.methven.art@hotmail.co.uk. Thank you for the ongoing support and I look forward to hearing from you. Don't forget that I will be livestreaming every Friday at 2pm GMT LONDON time on Picarto TV. Come and join the madness! picarto.tv/MadMunchkin

description: SPEEDPAINT!!! www.youtube.com/watch?v=m1CWfV… Hello friends! This is a Patreon reward for all Â£20 supporters of my comic, Between the Vale! They will get the full-sized, un-watermarked wallpaper version The story behind this image is how Dar'Akunai, the Eldest of the Dragons, became the most powerful dragon in the world. In this world, the dragons fell from the stars as meteors, or "dark stars". The dragons grew and formed around the meteor, and it became their hearts. Each dragon is born with a finite amount of magical energy, which can be utilised through their breaths. Most dragons only use their breath attacks sparingly, as each time they breathe fire/ice (or pure cosmic energy as is the case with Akunai) they lose part of their energy. When they use up all of their energy reserves, they die. But Akunai was greedy. He learned that if he devoured his own kind, he would gain their magical energies. His meteor heart became so full that it has begun to crack his mortal vessel. Akunai grew so large and so powerful that the rest of the dragons of the Vale have gone into hiding, fearing for their lives. Akunai gave himself the title of "Dar", meaning "Lord" in the language of the gods, though his own kind simply refer to him as The Cannibal. You can check out the webcomic here! www.webtoons.com/en/challenge/… Or you can support the comic on Patreon! www.patreon.com/SmallBeanStudi…

description: I drew this several years ago for a line of merchandise at Cafepress - T-shirts, keychains, mousepad and wall clock. (I think I might have sold two shirts.) This is a redrawn version of My favorite Tetsuko drawing; I thought I'd "improve" the drawing by fixing a few of the things I thought could be improved in the original drawing (like wider hips); I also thought she needed a bikini top that fit better. But when I was done, I found that I still liked the original better. Still, I figured that the newer art better reflected my style at the time, so I used this art in the Cafepress merchandise. A couple of years ago, I also started a store at TeePublic, because it offered better artist margins. For the T-shirts I sell there, I decided to do a re-tracing of the first drawing, keeping it as close to the original as possible (except for the better-fitting bikini). This version posted here by request of a fan who follows me here and at my Patreon page. Tetsuko's Swag at Cafepress T-shirts at TeePublic

description: LAZER-HAWK ORIGIN Lieutenant-Commander Ayala Rannz is a Praxian space explorer from Planet Praxis. She was an Officer in the Alliance defense fleet but resigned from her duty because of the immense bureaucracy there. She joined Galacta-Force instead to make a positive difference in the Galaxy and underwent exposure to Omni particles which gave her the ability of Laser Manipulation and Telepathy. Now she helps to keep the peace across the Galaxy as Lazer-Hawk. PERSONAL DATA Characteristics: Â· Species: Praxian Â· Age: 32 Â· Height: 5’11” Â· Weight: 124lbs Â· Eye Color: Violet Blue Â· Hair Color: Black (with luminescent strands) Â· Skin Color: Violet Status Â· Place of Birth: Praxis Â· Citizenship: Betrassus Â· Base: The Ixion Interceptor, Galactor Prime (Galacta-Force Headquarters) Â· Occupation: Space Explorer, Diplomat Â· Known Relatives: Mevtr Rannz(Father), Slexi Rannz(Mother), Kotva Ranzz(Older Brother, Deceased), Kryx tol Rannz(Older Brother), Ryruul(Little sister), Cozhana(Youngest sister), Ivtr Razz(Her C.O and FiancÃ©e, Deceased) . POWERS AND ABILITIES Power Grid Â· Intelligence: 4 Â· Strength: 4 Â· Speed: 7 Â· Durability: 3 Â· Energy Projection: 5 Â· Fighting Skills: 6 Laser Manipulation: Lazer-Hawk can create, shape and manipulate laser light, intense, coherent, monochromatic, parallel beam of light (infrared, visible, or ultraviolet) or other electromagnetic radiation, which is composed of waves of the same frequency and all in phase. Laser Attacks: she can create and project beams of laser that are capable of piercing virtually anything they come in contact with and have explosive properties Holographic Projection: she can create, shape and manipulate holograms, fully three-dimensional images of the holographed target Light speed: She is able to transform her body into living laser and can travel at the speed of light. Telepathy: She has the ability to mentally receive and transmit information. Enhanced Condition: Thanks to her genetic enhancements her body is at peak physical and mental condition which means that she is faster, stronger and smarter than anyone from her own race. Flight: Lazer-Hawk has the ability to fly and can perform interstellar space travel on her own Vacuum Adaptation: She has the ability to adapt to the vacuum of space unaided LIMITATIONS Â· May be unable to create laser, being limited to manipulating only from already existing sources. Â· She is limited to controlling lasers within a certain radius. Â· Her light attacks are ineffective against mirrored surfaces and may bounce off of them Â· She is vulnerable to Gravitational attacks SKILLS As a former member of the Alliance fleet she received advanced training in hand to hand and space combat. Thanks to her telepathic abilities she is Omni-lingual and is able to speak and understand any alien language fluently making her an expert in the art of diplomacy PARAPHERNALIA Her suit is specifically tailored to her power set and it is equipped with sufficient kinetic barriers to shield against energy and projectile based weaponry and can generate its own life support field when in deep space. The suit also comes with a protective navigation visor which she uses when in battle or making interstellar space travel PERSONALITY Ayala is more of a people person and has this ability to make someone feel good about his or herself. Though she is not very expressive in her behaviour she is a very sophisticated woman who has captivating charm and elegant taste. She has this nurturing personality about herself that draws people to her and will readily help a teammate or someone in need. She believes in diplomacy before violence but there are times where she may drop those ideals and do what must be done for the greater good. She is very intelligent and knows how to talk to people of different backgrounds. However she feels uncomfortable taking the role of a leader. But when the situation calls for it she will give it her all and lead her team to victory. She dreams of a peaceful Galaxy and will fight to make that dream a reality.

description: So here's my OC, Lacey Highwater. For those of you who are unfamiliar with the character, she comes from a (yet unnamed) fictional, Steampunk-inspired world. She's somewhat of a feminist character, and would be considered tomboyish compared to the more "proper" way that women are supposed to be portrayed in her era. She has a steam-powered motorcycle of sorts, which she uses to get around. Her full back-story and additional characters aren't fully developed yet, but I hope to further develop her world/story in the future. She would be the main protagonist/hero of the story, though! I haven't drawn her for a while, and felt that I wanted to update her look slightly, while keeping the feel of the original. I made her belt more functional, instead of just being a flashy way to hold the key to her ride! I tried out some new stuff with the colouring technique, which I'm thinking of doing a lot more often now, since I like the result! To see some of my older pieces (with varying quality) featuring Lacey, click here: [link] Special thanks to for all his help throughout the process; especially with his help in fixing an issue in the pose, during the early stages of the piece! Used bits of this tutorial, to make the map in the background: [link] Anyways, I hope you dig the piece! Lacey Highwater (c) Spidersaiyan/Luis Neto ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Edit: Thanks for the DD! I really appreciate it! As sort of a way of saying thanks, I thought I'd upload the process for this piece.

description: As we bid adieu to 2015, I'd just like to share one last memory that almost slipped through the proverbial cracks. So there I was, last May, driving down Main Street on a quiet Wednesday morning. Its one of those cute Main Streets with lots of shops and cafes, but early enough that it was still fairly quiet. Now, I have a sort of Spidey sense for when an attractive woman is about. An itch at the back of my mind. And it starts pinging like crazy! I look over in front of the post office and see this very fit young lady bending over in a way I thought women only did in pornos, her wee skirt riding up over her ass, rummaging for something in her purse. The street was relatively empty of pedestrians at that point, but I almost crashed the Gao Mobile into the car in front of me! I glanced up in my rear view mirror, and the guy in the work van behind me (who almost crashed into me) was practically chewing on his steering wheel at the display! When I got home, I jotted down a quick sketch to preserve the memory, and I promptly forgot about it until I noticed the sketch and decided to finish it up as a farewell to 2015. --- If you enjoy my work here on DeviantArt, please consider supporting me on Patreon! www.patreon.com/gao23

description: Close-ups: wallpaper: A lot of people assume that this a purely fictional and fantasy background when in fact it was an ACTUAL dream that I had. despite its heavily fantasy themed this was the nature dream. Theoritically, due to the fact this comes the subconscious mind, it classifies as a subtly surreal piece. Fantasy appears to be is subject matter, but not its style, fantasy is not a style but a subject matter. And yes i dream in fantasy ... a lot. i mean i play fantasy RPG's, dnd, write fantasty stories and the like. Its always on the go in my head so it always seeping into my dreams. the only times it doenst it when i have a major problem in real life or a have a toxic dream resulting in zombies. Peoples view on surrealism is that it needs to look like Dali, if this is the case then art movement princples are ignore for the sake of 'copying' a artists style of drawing. but enough of that, i dont profess to be a surrealist artist. all i can vouch for is that the subject matter of this piece was from a genuine dream. and really that all i can say. --------------------------------------------------------------------- Okay, this needs a bit of explaining. The orange fairies are dreams, muses and sources of inspiration. The glowing girl is me, my inner child. the Bogloid holding my hand is my guardian to protect me while i sleep and to help gather muses and inspirations for me. the large tree with the glowing doorway is my mind, where all my ambisions and memories are kept. Inside of there these muses are turned into works of art the sprout from the tree. this mostly based on an ACTUAL dream i had. when i was little i had terrible night terrors, i had a stuffed toy of a monster and my mum told me it was to protect me while i sleep. EDIT: Stronger shadows and lights on bogloid, blur lighting round doorway, tuned lighting around paintings (Thanks *Carsis!) all crits welcome!

description: A sneaky peeky frame from The Fire and the Phoenix Episode 2 Part 2. This is a frame that will be used in a "memory" sequence involving Torio, and his first wife, Osyrion (Onarius's twin sister, and the aunt our protagonist, Ozzy, is named after). She died during the Ujorkas Uprising when a wyvern spit venom into her eyes and mouth. It was a few months later when Torio met his current wife, Malina. The image is supposed to be fuzzy and kind-of blurry to represent a memory. It's not be best piece, but I thought you'd be interested in seeing the face behind the name :3

description: Another Crossover Project that features two of my favorite tv franchises form the past many years. This time, takes place in an alternate timeline when the Mutagen Bomb exploded in New York and all over the Planet, mutating all humans into monterous freaks. This in turn the world into a mutant inhabitant wasteland. Only the Rainbooms and the Turtles manage to survive, with he help of a meerkat mutant into finding an oasis paradise to live in peace. Note: I gave Leo two large Katana/Buster Swords in addition his traditional Blue Ninja Mask, just for sentimental reasons. Magic Spark is sorta based off of the Mad Max Film that the fic and two part episode was based off on. Leonardo 2012 (Blue Maximus Kong) Twilight Sparkle 2015 (Magic Spark) Spike The Dog 2015 (Wolfatizer) Request By jebens1 Credit of the FanFiction goes to DarkMagicianmon Source For Twilight's outfit: jebens1 Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (2012-2017) My Little Pony Equestria Girls (2013-Present)

description: For 's contest! I chose the category "Socialising", and decided to draw my character Aeluris interacting with Hops's character Harvin! I thought that, if they ever met, Aeluris would be fascinated with Harvin. It is her life's ambition to know all there is to know, and the chance to learn from a mechanical owl would be a dream come true for her! I'm sure Harvin would find Aeluris to be charming company, as she would listen to his lectures and study hard under his teaching. However, she may be tempted to dismantle the owl to figure out his inner workings.

description: This is the 2nd (kind of) commission from Eric [link] for his and Keri's character, Olga Svenson. My first attempt (Olga vs Clovie) was a little off the mark but this version shows her character off a lot better, plus it's quite nice and bright with no destruction! The original pencil sketch was inked and then scanned into photoshop, cleaned up and digitally rendered. I'm pretty happy with this one, especially the reflection as it's not just a straight forward copy, rotate and paste job (which I found out the hard way!) Thanks very much to Eric and Keri for their commission, please check out his Shag49931's page at the above link to see more of their characters and commissions.

description: After I watched Rainbow Rocks, I just felt like drawing Sunset Shimmer, since she was such a great character in that movie. What's awesome about "good" Sunset is that she still feels "dangerous"; The kind that, if she saw you acting out of line, would think nothing of pulling you into some dark corridor and saying "You listen: I may be nice now. But I wasn't always like this. I've done things, and I know things. Things that are not nice at all, and that I'd be glad to show you if you ever mess with me or my friends. Capiche?" So, yeah, pretty awesome character arc. Holy crap, I'm getting better at painting fire! o_O

description: Three years ago, I made this adjustment to the classic Cartoon Network movie opening: nemalki.deviantart.com/art/Thi… On October 1, 1992, Turner Broadcasting introduced the world to their newest cable channel, Cartoon Network. Its mission was decent, honest, and uncomplicated: air the best in animation 24 hours a day, seven days a week. No live-action. No agenda to push said live-action. And completely ran by people who gave a damn about animation. On the network's 20th anniversary, I present this piece, a modernization of the Cartoon Network "movie theater" scene with many of the shows on the network circa 2001. A lot has changed, and I've reflected that. And yes, I did include Adult Swim characters and TOM from Toonami, who wasn't included in the original. I included some DC characters like Robin from Teen Titans, Wonder Woman from Justice League, Superman, Batman from Brave and the Bold, Green Lantern from his self-titled series, and Artemis from Young Justice. I also put in some third-party shows like Total Drama, Yumi from Code Lyoko, Goku from DBZ, Sailor Moon, and Johnny Test (though I know lots of you guys and gals aren't fans, but it is a part of the network's history). Yes, I am aware that a lot of shows are missing, particularly many third-party shows that aired on the network. I decided to do that because of three reasons: I wanted to celebrate Cartoon Network's 20th anniversary with shows that either debuted or aired exclusively on Cartoon Network or managed by Cartoon Network, I didn't want the picture to be full of shows that are more closely identified with other networks more than Cartoon Network (most people think of Kids' WB rather than CN when it comes to Pokemon or Yu Gi Oh, Fox Box or Nickelodeon when it comes to Winx Club or Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, and Fox when it comes to stuff like Family Guy, King of the Hill, and American Dad), and if I just put every single acquisition Cartoon Network made in this piece, there wouldn't be any room for any of the Cartoon Network stuff (and I barely had enough room for the Cartoon Network shows that I could fit in). And those looking at this in 2016 and beyond, take note this piece was created in 2012, and lots of shows currently on the lineup, including Steven Universe, Uncle Grandpa, Clarence, and a few others weren't on when this was made. Maybe if I make a piece in 2017, I'll definitely include them. And no live-action. At all. Wait, no, that's not true. Fleegle from the Banana Splits is here, but he doesn't really count for live-action. Unlike the previous piece, I did this from scratch. Empty theater, and looking for the right pictures for this piece. Lots of characters, lots of work. So, without much more commentary, happy 20th birthday Cartoon Network.

description: Just a quick little drawing of Frisk post-DT extractions in The Rivers Warning comic. Figured I'd share. Source for the sign language: www.lifeprint.com/asl101/pages… WITH REGARDS TO FRISKS GENDER IN MY COMIC: I don't care. I can't overstate how much I don't care. They are whatever gender you want to see them as. Just like in the game, it is open to your own interpretation. The topic of gender really doesn't matter to the story I'm trying to tell - so I haven't bothered to think about it. And when I'm saying, 'eh, doesn't matter' - that doesn't mean Frisk doesn't have a gender, is nonbinary, or whatever. It just means I don't care or make it my business in deciding what their gender is. Male, female, both, neither, that is up to you to decide on an individual level. It's ambiguous in the game, it'll be ambiguous in the comic - whether they're genderless, male, or female, that'll be up to you to decide as an individual reader. Whatever pronouns you decide to use for Frisk are completely valid and acceptable. There is no wrong answer, here. Please stop witch-hunting people you think are using the 'wrong' pronouns. They're just interpreting the character in their own preferred way. Please be respectful of that. Thank you.

description: Hey guys! I’ve just started funding for my short film “Fight and Flight” ! It’s a feel good-comedy about a young man who is framed for murder and must prove his innocence while handcuffed to the police officer arresting him! (So it's a lot of fun) (Are there any older hijack fans who remember this idea???) If you’d like to look into the project or maybe donate to help its progress please check out the indiegogo page right here! It would mean a lot if people shared this post or donated a little if you had a few dollars spare! (Literally every single dollar counts!) If you decide to help me out by donating please comment or send me a note so I can thank you personally because it would mean so much to me! If you can't afford it, and you still wanted to help you can share the link! Or you can share the post here on tumblr as well!! Thankyou everyone!! Separate note: ALSO THANKYOU FOR ALL THE ART REQUESTS LATELY. I've been so busy with funding and filming, but as soon as this all dies down I'll be drawing again! Sorry I've been gone so long! And of course, there's heaps of Spiderman and ladybug stuff coming your way!

description: This is a reworked version of this piece I did, I flipped it, changed Mary's face and had Maddy still crying but a happy cry. Now, I know, these two usually hate each other, or just tolerate each other. You've never seen these characters the way I have, and I know people joke about Mary being stupid, and Maddy always being so hateful and negative, but these two get me through a lot. I used to draw other characters when I needed cheering up, and now I have these two. It's really important to me to love yourself, and your creativity. Don't keep putting yourself down just because you don't think you're good enough. Keep pushing yourself to be better.

description: Click here to see the speed drawing! I actually really liked how this turned out?? I used around half the time I usually spend on making finished paintings, but it still worked out nicely. I'm not used to NOT spending half a day on these things. But can we just take a moment to talk about Blue Diamond? Cause she is my favorite space goddess at the moment. Seriously, I just wana give her a hug and say everything's gonna be alright. I know she's supposed to be a tyrant ruler with the other diamonds and all, but she deserves a little love <3 Other than that, have a wonderful rest of the day! Art(c) Video(c)

description: Holy crap, has it been a while since I posted anything. Check my blog for an update on that, because I'm gonna try posting some more from now on. Anyways, this is a picture of my character Faye Valentine (yes, I know there is another Faye Valentine in Cowboy Bebop, don't care) that I've whipped up with PS CS4 and my trusty Wacom. It was really more of an experiment in rendering since if you look at the rest of my gallery, it's laughably bad in terms of coloring and well...everything. Mad props to chuck-piresART who did the initial designs along with a bunch of pictures I commissioned him for, as well as providing me with a lot of inspiration for pallete and rendering style. Anyways, please leave a comment if you enjoy! Comments are fuel for my art!

description: At first Rapunzel was terribly frightened when a man such as she had never seen before came in to her. However, the prince began talking to her in a very friendly manner, telling her that his heart had been so touched by her singing that he could have no peace until he had seen her in person. Then Rapunzel lost her fear, and when he asked her if she would take him as her husband, she thought, "He would rather have me than would old Frau Gothel." She said yes and placed her hand into his. She said, "I would go with you gladly, but I do not know how to get down. Every time that you come, bring a strand of silk, from which I will weave a ladder. When it is finished I will climb down, and you can take me away on your horse. They arranged that he would come to her every evening, for the old woman came by day.

description: This was a commission for ~rowan4670. The concept and text were scripted by ~rowan4670. I am embarrassed to say that he asked for this commission back in 2007 and I didn't get it finished back then, due to all kinds of personal problems. Then it got so late that I was too ashamed to come back to dA for a long time. Coming back now, I felt that the least I should do was to complete the commission that was so very long overdue. The weird thing about this one is that I actually did the linework drawing and inking back in 2007 but colored it in 2010. So it is an odd mix of skill levels for me.

description: The new and improved version of my Field Guide to Heavy Metal Satan Fingers. Done so I can submit it as a print... ROCK ON!!!! WAAAAaaaAAAAaaaAAA! *deedly deedly dee!* (shredding guitar solo!) \m/!!!!!!! NOTE: No matter how much the "inverse Satan" looks like Dane Cook's "Super Finger," I came up with it independently, not seeing the SuFi until well after the fact. And, I'd like to point out that the Mr. Cook's "Super Finger" logo is inaccurate, since the thumb should be folded over the other fingers, not sticking out to the side. That's poor graphic design, that is! Also, yes, I know it's also called the Devil Horns, Hook'em Horns, the Malocchio (from Dio's grandmother, who used it to ward off the evil eye). "Heavy Metal Satan Figures" just sounds funnier.

This time, takes place during the Equestria Ninjas Movie Fic, where the group of heroes travel to Mount Aries to seek help of from the Hippogriffs, only to discover that their is underwater life, Seaquestria , inhabited by Seaponies aka the Hippogriffs. description: I'm trying to see if there is a limit to how many times I can upload the same picture with only minor changes. I finished drawing Hank's legs and, because of the awkward way in which he falls off the page, I decided that it might help to fill that empty space on the right with another character. I ended up drawing Hank's best buddy, Bobby, in there because I wanted to experiment around with different ways of representing his ice form. I think the jury is still out on whether this piece is 100% successful or not; but, for better or worse, I think it's time to move on to something else.

So I did a quick picture of them instead of going to bed (which I am sure I will regret in the morning when I wake up tired and spent half the morning in a zombie-like state). They look so tasty! Japan comes out with some of the coolest snack foods! I wouldn't be able to live without wasabi peas, instant ramen, and pocky. Now I want to buy konpeito!

description: NEW SERIES!!! Speedpaint: www.youtube.com/watch?v=BESGqH… Hello friends I am excited to announce the my new comic series that I'm collaborating on with my boyfriend - Between the Vale! The prologue of Between the Vale tells the story of four of the world's greatest heroes and their most important adventure - to seal away the magical creatures who threaten to destroy their home! Yes, I know the main characters are humans (well, only one of the characters you see here is human. The others are an elf, a dwarf, an Old God and a big ol dragon), but if you're a fan of my series The Fire and the Phoenix you'll like this one too! We've put just as much effort into the lore, worldbuilding and characters as TFatP, and I'm enjoying working on it just as much! I'm hoping you'll check it out Characters in the foreground are: - Baltham (Elven Knight in golden armour) - Mier (Curly-haired human eating an apple) - Ethelion (Scarecrow-looking wizard in the wide-brimmed hat) - Brina (Female dwarf with a sweet 'stache) Where to find the comic: RIGHT HERE! Patreon: www.patreon.com/SmallBeanStudi… This is the main base of operation. The first three pages have been released, and a new page will be released every week! There are rewards available to those who pledge $2 or more, such as exclusive character dossiers and stories, painted wallpapers and the chance for your character to appear in the comic! Tapastic: tapas.io/series/Between-The-Va… View the comic conveniently and it will be updated every week! Thank you so much <3 Hope you enjoy!
