description: We all have a special someone in our lives. It happens at all levels, from family to your best friend. Some more platonic and others more romantic. We go through our lives searching for a partner, why should anything hold us back from being with that person we love? A bit of a celebration piece for the bill that passed recently passed making Same sex marriage 100% legal in the United States. There is still a long batle ahead to get full equal rights for same sex couples but this is a step in the right direction. I hope you all like this piece. Had a lot of fun doing it.

description: Today I'm presenting you a new member of L.A Kaiju FAM! His name? Yogang Star! His name comes from the japanese for lava, Yogan, plus gangsta. Would be like lava gangsta...and in fact he is made of lava and black magma and loves gangsta rap! He's Mudds' older big bro and once he looked like Mudds, but his strong desire to wear a pair of awesome sneakers (he LOVES sneakers) made him evolve and develop longer legs. He's fast and strong and jumps as high as if he was flying. He's well respected among the L.A Kaiju FAM members, and a good comrade to Don Antler. Mudds also respects him as brother and wishes to be like him someday. You can check Yongang Star's shirt here: And for you guys new to L.A Kaiju FAM: L.A Kaiju FAM (Los Angeles Kaiju Family) is a mafia, a gang if you want, formed by Kaijus (japanase term for big and weird monster) from all over the world. They have fun bullying cities and making heroes suffer and if someone mess with them, they just destroy his city and eat up the whole population. They have their headquarters somewhere in Los Angeles. Nobody can explain how their location hasnt been discovered yet, considering their size!

description: 121 Marvel characters rendered in a diversity of minimalist styles. They continue to be listed alphabetically, with three exceptions: 1) The classic Fantastic Four are together because they're designed differently, modeled after the movie posters of Saul Bass. 2) The Runaways appear together because of a few things that make their designs unique, including the inclusion of 2 characters on each. (I guess that means I have 124 characters here--125 if you include Lockheed with Shadowcat!) Don't worry, fans, Xavin and Karolina will be coming soon. 3) The Wrecking Crew are together, because they too are a bit distinctive in their designs and--let's face it, Piledriver on his own is lame.

description: Another Crossover Project that features two of my favorite tv franchises form the past many years. This time, takes place during the Equestria Ninjas Movie Fic, where the group of heroes travel to Mount Aries to seek help of from the Hippogriffs, only to discover that their is underwater life, Seaquestria , inhabited by Seaponies aka the Hippogriffs. The group then experience life for a while before things got a little ugly. Note: I consider making Leo and his brothers sea turtle hybrids due to their mutant DNA, including their little anthro pony ears and hairs. Karai, obviously a seapony like the mane 6 with capability to change into her serpent form. As for Blade, I have been informed to make him Seapony Hybrid, due to his mutant DNA Leonardo 2012 Princess Twilight Sparkle 2013 Karai 2012 Spike The Dragon 2011 Blade Swipe OC 2017 Credit of the FanFiction goes to DarkMagicianmon Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (2012-2017) My Little Pony Equestria Girls (2013-Present)

description: OK, I had an idea, and I'm still not sure about the end result, but here you go. (I also thought about this WAY more than I should have. My sincerest apologies to Lauren Faust. ) Inspired in part by Watership Down, I created a personification (ponysonification? ) of death for the My Little Pony: Friendship Is Magic universe (because I'm more than slightly unhinged) . I couldn't help wondering how death would happen for them, it being a magical land and all, so I hit on the idea that there would be some sort of entity that oversees the whole thing, just as Luna and Celestia deal with the moon and sun. And like Luna, she has different forms, though hers have nothing to do with being evil or power-hungry. Macaria's forms depend entirely on whom she is visiting, and their deeds in life would determine how they see her. In the case of a good, hard-working pony like Granny Smith, she would appear in this form because Granny Smith's good soul would cause her to see Death this way. A pony who had spent their life being evil, without truly repenting of their evil deeds, would see her in her other form, Hecate. (I'll be posting that version in a few days. ) If, for instance, a good pony and a bad pony were seeing her at the same time, they would still see her differently from one another. Because her appearance is based entirely on the perception of those she brings to the afterlife, no one actually knows her true form. Running with the Greco-Roman motif often invoked in the show (Celestia, Luna, Tartarus, Ursa Minor, etc. ) , I named her Macaria. In Greek Mythology, Macaria was the daughter of Hades and represented a 'blessed death' , i.e. she who ruled over the souls of those who had lived good lives. I thought that was a good fit, so I went with it. However, she would have many names depending on regional language differences. Macaria is how Twilight Sparkle etc. would know her. Zecora, on the other hand, would know Macaria by another name from her own language, and would have her own culture's stories surrounding her. I wanted Macaria to look related to the ponies whose souls she was guiding to the afterlife, but still somewhat alien, so I based her looks on the Windigoes from the Hearth's Warming Eve episode. That way, she would seem even more 'god-like' in appearance than the royal sisters (because, you know, Death. ) She's still got a cutie mark, but it's more for the sake of familiarity. Also, to make the whole thing streamlined, she rules over death for ALL of the creatures of that world, including zebras and griffons and such, so this is just the form she uses with ponies. Maybe someday, if I really lose my mind, I might try and draw her griffon/zebra/whatever form. We'll see. To the good, Macaria is gentle and merciful, and helps to ease their way into the new and potentially frightening realm of death. She's especially tender with those who die very young. However, death comes to all at some point, so she is also impartial in that regard. There is no escaping her, no matter how kind or beautiful she is. Unless Luna and Celestia, or any other beings in that world, turn out to actually be immortal and not just nearly immortal, they will eventually have to meet her like anyone else. All good souls are guided to the Elysian Fields (woo Greek mythology! ) by Macaria to spend eternity with their loved ones. (Or, if they were evil in life, to wander around alone and in darkness for eternity. Because a show for kids really needs this. Anyway, more on that part of Macaria's realm when I post the other half of this picture. ) It is important to note that Macaria/Hecate walks among the beings of the MLP world all the time, but a pony can only see her if they're dead/on the point of death. Or, in rare cases, she will appear to warn or comfort, but it is almost always her lot to wander their world unseen and unknown by the living. At most, living beings will feel her presence where there has been death, but that feeling varies with the manner of death/individual feeling her presence. I'm sure most of you won't care to read this, which is fine. My brain wouldn't turn off until I stuffed myself full of turkey and passed out, so be thankful this explanation isn't a LOT longer. I'd be interested to know what other people have come up with for the ponysonification of death for this world, because I can't be the first to have thought about this. Note: Granny Smith is just here to be an example of a good pony. I PROMISE I DIDN'T KILL HER OFF. O__O Other half here: Group shot:

description: Amber- the Element of Earth. Amber's designs... has changed around so much- just not satisfied. NEEDLESS TO SAY, I'm quite satisfied now. So I went back to her old design and decide that perfect straight hair suited her more, goes with her body; TALL and very voluptuous ( Kat calls her the Amazon) and since she masks most of her emotions, the bangs really suit her. Kinda was inspired for Anna Torv for the face- been watchin Fringe as of late and I love Anna's jaw structure. So A little background on her as she has not be really explained before: BATTLE-WISE: I don't really have Amber's power make earthquakes (maybe later), mostly because she believes in not manipulating the forces of nature for the use of destruction. It's a chaotic power after all. Since the earth's essence is well, her soul- Any source of it- be it sand, plant or rocks she is absolutely connected. She also connected to it by her senses which is one reason Amber is so introverted to saving humans as she believes that they are 'poisoning' the earth. These extra earthy- senses makes her an excellent tracker. She does however speed up the growth of plants at remarkable speed and can manipulate its movement. Most of her strongest attacks, literally start by a seed. Most of her weapons including her arrows have a plant seed that she has cultivated and when that arrow pierces flesh- she can literally turn her foes body into the seeds incubator and manifestly destroy her enemy from the inside out. Amber's aim is also notoriously accurate. If she missed, she missed on purpose. Along with the power of growth, she is also a healer. With her knowledge of plants and the powers itself. She can turn herself INTO the earth. Plant, rock, dirt you name it... Makes her a great spy AND Makes having her long hair easier to braid since it well, can pretty much braid itself. QUIRKS: Hates technology. Any man-made object disgust her just due to fact she's narrow minded and and cannot except the change in the world. So yes, a bit of a Hippie... But seems to hate most demons more. Also loves books (the irony) basically the walking directory of demons and their tales. Uh... doesn't really like men- pretty much sees them only as lecherous, unintelligent fools. Gonna have to change THAT*winks* ... Enter the skirt-chasing, charming, Cajun demon hunter. Will do another one of Kat (That earlier one was for a test) I want to have something with her actually USING her powers. But up next will be EAGLE (Wind) Elements Â© 2013 Jac Taylor

description: As soon as I started thinking about this piece, I had something special in mind. I liked this pic of Supes and Bats [link] and wanted to do something similar. Then along came these two. John Talbot: Magic Energy/Energy Blaster [link] This haunted and broken ex-astronaut was given amazing energy-based powers, a new physique and a new life by a 'shard' fragment of Reality's ancient restoration and maintenance device, The Source Stone. Co-Founder and Earth-based Commander of Paragon's 'The Cerulean Legion', a small team of self-appointed "space-cops" also empowered The Source Stone. Husband of Legion Honor Guard Kirste Kallunki. Half-brother of StormForce's Frankie Carter. The Hornet: Science Martial Arts/Regeneration Scrapper [link] Master detective, hero, inventor, world class martial artist and 5th Column sleeper agent. This King's Row protector loves barbeque pork sandwiches (with extra pickles and mustard), strawberry-rhubarb pie, robots and his beautiful little dark mutant girlfriend, Frankie Carter. ...Oh yeah, and he's also a clone of the schizophrenic assassin, Recoil. Former owner of the now-defunct heroes-for-hire business, Operatives Inc. Current co-leader of the Steel Canyon-based supergroup StormForce's special operations unit. This was fun to do and turned out almost exactly how I wanted it. Now, let's hope the creator likes it as much.

description: Once upon a time, a young, innocent Gao knew a lovely woman named Melissa. Melissa was, in short, a sort of real life Jenny. While she was quite smart, she also was a bit ditzy and oblivious. She was also, like Jenny, built like the proverbial brick shithouse. Not fat - she was a cheerleader - but very very curvy in all the right places! She had an incredible chest. Easily D cups, but Melissa had not quite wised up to this fact yet- her bras were always a size or two too small. Her ample bosom was always spilling over the tops of her cups. She also had juicy thick hips and a nice round ass. Poor Melissa was always trying to wear denim miniskirts like the other girls wore, but her righteous booty was always making the skirts ride up dangerously high, exposing long lovely glimpses of her American thighs and often a bit more. So on this particular day, Melissa had worn a blouse to school that had way too many buttons running down the front. She was running late getting changed after gym class, and didn't have time to button them all up. She came bouncing into English class with her overworked bra and bountiful cleavage spilling everywhere, completely oblivious to the astounding display of flesh she was putting on. Of course, one of her killjoy friends clued her in, and she quickly buttoned up, red-faced, but not before the whole class (and teacher) got a long, delicious look at those amazing breasts of hers. --- If you enjoy my work here on DeviantArt, please consider supporting me on Patreon! www.patreon.com/gao23

description: Task Force X :The Suicide Squad are taking a little R & Rin the Mediterranean. The team is spending some down-time by playing amateur archeologists on a long forgotten Greek isle. While digging in a grotto, Karin discovers a beautiful earthen jar. Inside the jar is a beautiful sparkling necklace. She feels a strange compulsion to try it on. When she does, she is possessed by the spirit of Circe! Her clothes are transformed to sparkling white, and her hair would have a tiara and maybe some leaves for decorations (ala Hollywood Greek goddess). When Rick confronts her, Circe transforms him into a merman! If you are interested in your own commission please private message me.

description: okay, before you attack me for being a complete psycho... it's not as bad as all that. it's just a refurbished panel from a favorite little sight-gag page i did. Socke is running along with Say-Goodnight Gracie on a rope-leash to keep her from toddling off. they come over a rise and Socke sees their friend Heath in the distance. Say-Goodnight is much shorter and can't see, so Socke lifts her (by the leash) so she can. of course, being a ragdoll, she just naturally assumes that limp position! Socke is the guy i told you about in earlier stories who brought to life Mister McBunbun, then used the same technology to mass-produce the Say-Goodnight Gracies. when the little Say-Goodnight Gracie depicted here (sometimes reffered to as Raggedy Anarchist) got tangled in the machine that produced the dolls and caused a fire, Socke returned to find his entire livleyhood burned to ashes. in a moment of passion, he shot himself in the head. Mr. McBunbun and Say-Goodnight salvaged what they could of the amazing machine and used it to fasion socke a prosthetic head. the only material available to them at the spur of the moment is the sock on Socke's foot. oh yeah -- and i know his hands are wierd. they're work gloves.

description: UPDATE FOR CURRENT DRAWFRIEND: MEGAOOPS! I was trying to announce my Art Stream on EQD last night and some wires got crossed on their end...and they put the "sample" for the stream up as a Drawfriend! I know it's a repost, and it wasn't intended to be. I'm really sorry for any confusion, but my intent was simply to stream...not to repost an old image to the drawfriend! I love you guys! *** UPDATE (2011): I've noticed that the file I put up here was partly corrupted by the saving process (adding unwanted artifacts!). I've now corrected the file so it doesn't have any of the artifacts anymore. I also uploaded a larger one! I would like to say thank you to all who have Favorited this piece. I've been trying to thank you all personally, but DA thinks I'm spamming. XP I will get to it soon though! Another note - if you have been poking through my gallery or intend to, understand that I haven't posted anything current on my DA in nearly 5 years. I wasn't drawing much for the longest time - but MLP has brought back some of the magic that I used to feel while drawing. It's a very remarkable show! *** As suggested by a brony from the MMO-Champion Brony thread. No one really draws Star Swirl the Bearded (though I did manage to find a few images of him) - and since he's supposedly the most epic unicorn of all time, why not do an epic picture of him? Yeah. And stuff. No stealing him, because it's my art and Hasbro's character and I will MISH anyone who steals my art! This is the first time I attempted a background in the MLP:FIM style and I think it turned out pretty well. Note: His beard, tail and mane are pinkish because I found that white looked far too boring - so I made him match the G4 version of Star Swirl (even though she's a mare!) - so...yeah. And stuff. Took about 8 hours of working + diddling around. XD PS7. My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic AND Star Swirl the Bearded are (c) Hasbro.

description: Every now and then I get into arguments with people on what makes someone a 'true' artist, and that's usually with people who have never bought a paintbrush in their life. Today's argument was with someone who said there is no emotion in digital art, and that the computer does all the work for you. Well, this is digital art. I was in tears drawing this. Look at how much emotion is in Maddy's face because she doubts herself as an artist because of what was said to me today. She is so upset and angry at herself that she runs and hugs a character that...whether she likes it or not, represents her creativity. That raw, unchecked crazy spontaneous creativity that can't be controlled. But it can be embraced. Mary Sue being unable to be sad just hugs her and smiles reassuringly. They may fight and often hate each other because of their differences but they're stuck with each other. They can't live without each other. The artist and her creativity personified. In a way they complete each other. I feel this picture shows both sides of the emotions of being an artist; it's not easy, it can be torture. But it's so much fun and brings so much happiness to people because they can express what they can't put into words. No matter if you use traditional or digital or a healthy balance of both. Your creativity comes from YOU. Not the tools you use. Don't let ANYONE tell you otherwise. EDIT: This year, my grandad on my mum's side purchased this piece from me. Sadly he died rather suddenly in October 2016, so now this piece is my favorite piece of Maddy and Mary together.

description: Day 30: Your choice! I decided to defer my choice to those of you who've written in during this challenge, noticing that I've been drawing Sonya with a "healthy" amount of muscle tone, and wanted to see her flexing. Also decided to do it in color, because.

description: Epic Edit: Holy hell I've daily deviated! I spent two weeks doing this for my portfolio today. It was the reviewer's favorite thing and told me to keep it in there. Success! I don't care if it's retarded and not even funny. As long as I got a on this strip to be in my portfolio, I'm a.o.k. because drawing this took many many and even more many hours. Atleast it didn't take a month+ like everything else. w00t! I have the sheep! --- You can tell the parts where I rushed it, but atleast they don't look that bad. I wanted to do some parts in a different perspective, but I was running out of time. The whole "I rushed this" also explains why it's not even funny. Or maybe it is and I've just looked at it so much that I just don't think it's funny anymore. If you don't know, it is a known fact that eggs blow up in microwaves. This will never be animated. I'm just too slow and busy to do so. It would be funnier if it was animated, because I would have fun doing the voice over, but it's too much work for me right now. Busy, busy, busy. Ramble, ramble, ramble. --- Taco, Egg, and the comic that takes an ass long time to load if you have dial-up(sucks for you) Â©Nicole F/=snow--skitty

description: Chalchiutlicue (Chal Chee-oo tlee kueh) another hard Aztec name. Also Called "She of the Jade skirt". Her nickname is Calamity Jade. She's my tomboy. She and Byrdi get along swimmingly. This chick could conceivably be very important for "No Evil" but I've not been able to design her till now. Everything I tried would always end up lookin' abysmal. I also could pick what her animal form was forever kept dancin around what it ought to be. The original Chalchiutlicue was associated with serpents but I didn't want her to be too much like Corn. I needed something associated with Faith, Water, Luck, and upstanding-ness in general. Jesus Christ Lizard it is!... Is that Blasphemy? Meh! And she can also play the part of the "Blue Lizard" if I feel like incorporating it. Brother Swan [link]

description: As many of you might not know (because it came to me as a surprise also) Iisjah is quite good with kids. He discovered it when his brother Urard made him watch over his daughter Cassandra from her earliest years. So here we have Iisjah, at Guernicas house, babysitting a small hoard of kids - his 8 year old twins Zoltan (redhead) and Suzanne (the blonde), on a weekly dad visit, his 11 year old niece Cassandra (brown haired) and Louis de Guernicas 11 year old daughter Julia (which Iisjah often babysits) They all are having a wonderful epic adventure full of magic and drama! Valiant hero Zoltan, riding on Iisjacorn, the prettiest and most magical unicorn in all the land, to face his pirate foes - one-eyed Casandra and captain Suzanne no-beard, which took the beautiful princess Julia prisoner. Epicness ensued. Iisjah is all nervous about that wooden sword - maybe making them wasn't such a good idea? And to think that Iisjah was a 'family-less orphaned as a child' guy just two years ago 8D Now he has massive family swarm xD Oh how they grow The painting in the back is heavily inspired by my childhood drawings Except the rainbow - I made mine fatter Where is Waldo? 8D ~~ A DD? Omhdsfgfuurrr I'm so happy! Thank you `touchedvenus and `kangel! Thank you to bits! Iisjah, Zoltan, Suzanne and Cassandra O'Riley, Julia (and Louis) de Guernica and art Â© Natalia Komuniewska More info about Iisjah here [link] [link] [link] [link] Texture by ~deathfetish

description: I have a few Christmas Fairs coming up and so needed to do some Christmas themed pictures. I settled on this one for the first piece. A Donkey and a reindeer take shelter from a snow storm in a cozy stable. The donkey represents the Christian religious side of Christmas while the Reindeer represents the more contemporary Christmas festivities. Both don't care about their differences; they just enjoy being together while they both rest.

description: I'VE DONE IT AGAIN!!! The very piece I have been pondering and wanting to do for bout a year but could not find the time to do so until now. The group that we all know and love embrace the Holiday Cheer. This design features the Turtles, Rainbooms and Human Allies as they all give a warm embrace of Christmas Cheer! A friend convinced me to have the Raimbooms, April, Karai and Shini dress up in their cute little elf outfits while the Turtles, Casey, and Spike the dog wear their Santa Claus Hats. Note: I had this done for two weeks but wanted to wait until Christmas Eve or Christmas Day to post this, just for the special occasion. I know that I said on the last design it was my last, but somehow I was all and inspired by the last design and after being convinced by a fellow follower and friend, I have decided to do this very special one, in dedication to the author of the Equestria Ninjas Fan Fictions (DarkMagicianmon) and to the followers of reading these fics and my designs (jebens1, TMNTony, rainbine94, lonewolf82084, and all the rest of you). This is for real this time, my final design piece til we hit 2018. I would still like to enjoy the rest of the Christmas month and New Years Eve-Day. So let me say again, Merry Christmas!! And A Happy New Year to all!! Source: www.fimfiction.net/story/39422… TMNT 2012-2017 (Leonardo "Leo," Raphael "Raph," Donatello "Donnie," Michelangelo "Mikey," April O'Neil, Casey Jones, Karai "Miwa" Hamato, and Shinigami) MLP EG 2013-Present (Twilight Sparkle, Sunset Shimmer, Applejack, Fluttershy, Pinkie Pie, Rarity, Rainbow Dash, and Spike the Dog)

description: Another awesome character I worked on created by the amazing jccomicsuniverse.deviantart.co… BIO The Girl With No Name is an ancient being that is nearly 20,000 years old. She is an abnormal hybrid between a Source, a Shift, and an Outlaw. As a Source, her control over element and reality-bending is beyond masterful. She is so overwhelmingly powerful, that her power almost constantly remains active. The same could not be said about her abilities as a Shift. Though the Shift species are limited, unlike most Shifts, she does not have complete mastery over time and/or space. Instead, her abilities are limited to allowing her to project herself and whoever accompanies her to the past, present or future but only as Astro projection of their selves with zero ability to interact with their non-present timeline. Though genetically she's classified as partly being affiliated with the Outlaw species, she bears no further relation outside of her DNA makeup. Unlike most unique beings, The Girl With No Name was born instead of being directly created by the deitic entities who control the universe. With so little known about this enigmatic being including her name and her whereabouts, The Girl With No Name is truly one of the most powerful mysteries of her universe.

description: '...my name is Darkstalker.' (Spoilers for Moon Rising and Winter Turning) --- I adore these two. I've wanted to draw them ever since I read Moon Rising, and after learning that Darkstalker is half IceWing I realized that Darkstalker would look absolutely awesome and so I HAD to draw him. Even though NightWings are described as either being black or dark purple I've always pictured Moonwatcher as being dark turquoise because of the cover of Moon Rising. Also because she's the first NightWing with mind reading and prophetic powers in generations I figured she should look unique. Also, unlike the villains from the first series who I found a bit bland (with the exception of Burn, she was awesome because of how nasty she was) I find Darkstalker very intriguing because we don't know whether or not he really is a bad guy. We know he was extremely powerful and ambitious, and would go to any end, even murder, to succeed, but he cared deeply for his friend Fathom and his mate Clearsight, and even forgave them after they betrayed him. He's also a very considerate mentor for Moon, and is surprisingly calm and collected after learning that he's been asleep for 2000 years. The fact that he has also never appeared in person yet is also pretty awesome. See Erins! This is how you write an interesting 3-Dimensional character! Darkstalker is awesome. description: Sorry Fluttershy Dear, the Smooze can be awfully... friendly. I don't think Flutters quite knows how to feel about this. So I watched the stream of the ep yesterday and I loved it. I do understand that a lot of people don't like how the smooze went from this disaster of evil to this happy-looking blobby thing that just kinda... blobs aroudn all adorably. But honestly I loved it, I thought it was arorable and funny. and really he just wants to be loved X3 and it was lovely gettign to see the Grand Galloping Gala again and the ponies all looked really cute in their new dresses. Fluttershy had this adorable peacock dress, though you can only see the underside of the dress part here lol Quick doodle for fun~ X3 and adorable. If you like my art and want nice hi-res files or just want to help me continue making it, please visit my Patreon ^-^

description: Before you say anything, yes this is inspired from Emala Jiss. I did not steal her idea, I just wanted to draw Pinkie Pie if she lost her element. That is all. Like my art? Commission me! Commission Prices (For Human Chibi and MLP)Before commissioning me, I would like for you to read the rules. If you do not read the rules and still send in a request for a commission, I will only link you back to here. RULES: I will not accept any commission based off of description. Please provide me a clear picture of your OC. If your OC was drawn traditionally, PLEASE take a clear picture and show some color on your character. It's not very easy trying to get the correct color from a colored drawing on paper on to a digital picture. Once you pay me, that is that. I do not do refunds, so you must be perfectly happy when I send you the sketch before paying. If I feel like your OC is too complicated to draw, I have the right to refuse your commission. So no complaining, please. Points are not accepted. If you feel like you can handle these rules, you can now look at the prices below. So here are the prices: $5 for a flat-colored picture. An additional $1 for another character.

description: I'VE DONE IT YET AGAIN!!! After a tearful argument, The Mane 6, Sunset and the Ninjas left Twilight alone to think things through. Twilight was sitting on the ledge, crying out from what has past. Leo and Spike caught up with her and try to comfort her. Here's a little script what I came up with: Spike- Twilight...its okay. You'll figure it out. You always do. Twilight- (Sniffling and Sobbing) No...I can't. I ruined everything! There's no chance in saving Equestria now! Leo went over to Twilight. Leo- Twilight... Twilight- IT'S ALL MY FAULT!! (Crying and Sobbing) Leo put his hand on Twilight's shoulder. She felt the warmth of his hand as she noticed him taking a knee next to her. Leo- Its not your fault Twilight. We’ll find some other way to stop the Storm King and Tempest. We always find another way. Twilight- (Sobbing) Not this time Leo. All is lost...because of me. Leo spoke in pride- No. I don’t believe so. Twilight-(Sobbing) Why didn't you two go with the others? Why did you come back after what I have said to Pinkie and out of anger, magic was released causing you to be hurt by me?” Twilight spoke between sobs, “You should hate me for that.” Leo- Twilight.....Look at me. Twilight opened her eyes and looked at Leo, still leaking in sorrow. Leo- I don’t hate you. We don’t hate you. We can never hate you. We’re still friends Twilight, no matter what or how difficult the situation is. If there’s one thing I have learned from all this, is that....friends don't quit on each other! They stick together to the end. Leo continued on stating on what good they all have done for a long period of time. Leo- Aside from the times that we both had separate, We both have faced other impossible odds together. We stopped the alien invasions from both the Kraang and the Triceratons, saving both our worlds from destruction, putting an end to the Shredder in his super mutagen form, helped Blade Swipe reunite with his sister, Melody and the rest of the ponies, and Even help Stygian from succumbing to the Pony of Shadows and reconcile with Starlswirl and the Pillars. Facing the Storm King and Tempest will be no different! We’ve been through a lot together, the good and the bad, with our friends. You even defended my life on Bleecker street from Shredder and his goons that one night in our world. You and your friends from CHS have shown all of us what the Magic of Friendship was really all about and we believed in it. The Twilight I know would never throw in the towel in the past encounters. And I’m certainly not gonna be the one that will let you do so! Friends don't quit on each other!! Twilight, upon hearing Leo’s words, snapped out for her sorrow. She then smiled a little bit and wrapped her arms around Leo in a tight embrace. Twilight- (Crying) Oh Leo.....I’m so sorry about what I said and did to you. Leo held Twilight close. Leo- It’s alright Twilight. Its gonna take a lot more than just a burst of magic to tear this bond apart. You are our best friend Twilight. The others still love you. My brothers still you. Spike still loves you......I still love you!! Twilight, heartwarmed by Leo’s words again, calmed herself down. Twilight- (Lighter sobs) Oohh, I love you too Leo! Spike, upon hearing this smiled. A few tears were leaking from his eyes as he placed his claws onto his chest, feeling this moment coming to pass. Twilight paused for a moment Twilight- You’re right though! We’ll find another way out of this mess together! Leo then smiled at Twilight’s recovery. Leo- But first things first, you need to make amends with the others. So let’s return and get things back on track. Twilight- Yes And I think you all can figure the rest from there. Pretty heartwrenching eh? The Fanfiction belongs to DarkMagicianmon

description: BUY THIS PRINT ON ETSY! www.etsy.com/uk/listing/386627… This was originally going to have Mary as Superman, but it didn't feel right drawing Mary without gloves. But then the idea of having her as Robin instead not only made it more fun to draw, it also solved the glove problem. For me, Mary's gloves are like Maddy's hat; they both must be wearing hat and gloves...though I am cheating here since Maddy is wearing the batman cowl and mask, but she gets away with it. Mary Sue is already so over powered that it would make sense to have her as Superman instead of Robin. But I think here the joke works; she can't possibly be Batman since he actually has character flaws that are likable. Maddy being Batman is just rediculous because she's so short. But her general demeanor makes it work. Have to admit, I loved drawing this one.

description: Update I've redrawn this comic, the updated version can be found here. This skit is loosely based on this clips from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, where Gilda the Griffin makes Fluttershy cry: (www.youtube.com/watch?v=3sHlZl…). It's sorta a re-match, but with a twist. Some of this comic is drawn from scratch in Photoshop using a mixture of brushes, layers and vectors. Other components have other sources, which I have favorited and linked to below. The ponies are based on images generated using General Zoi's pony Flash tool: (fav.me/d47efz4). I couldn't find a good image of Gilda from the series that I likes, so I created a posable Gilda using a combination of vectors, brushes and Photoshop layers. I used these images to get the look right, Sulyo's Roaring Gilda: (sulyo.deviantart.com/art/Gilda…), PeachSpice's Gilda Vector: (peachspices.deviantart.com/art…), and Elsdrake's Hippogriff Gilda: (elsdrake.deviantart.com/art/Hi…). The head in frame 4 was entierly drawn by Sulyo: (sulyo.deviantart.com/art/Gilda…), and is used here with their kind permission. As I couldn't draw one nearly good enough. The eye was also Created by General Zoi's pony Flash tool: (fav.me/d47efz4) for expediency\consistency. Fluttershy's Cutie Mark was created by Grendo11: (fav.me/d3jvy5x). As was Twilight Sparkle's Cutie Mark: (grendo11.deviantart.com/art/Tw…). In case you're wondering, the strange markings on Fluttershy's face in frame 8 is supposed to be a shadow of Gilda as she is overcome by Fluttershy's curse. The Library scene in frame 9 and frame 10 was created by RilDraw, the original can be found here : (fav.me/d4i2zoh). Those of you who grew up in the 1980s may recognize Fluttershy's magic chant as a slightly modified version of Darkstorm's spell of decay. To see this in its full resolution, please download.

description: I gotta say I really dig this Helmet design, don't you? LAZER-HAWK ORIGIN Lieutenant-Commander Ayala Rannz is a Praxian space explorer from Planet Praxis. She was an Officer in the Alliance defence fleet but resigned from her duty because of the immense bureaucracy there. She joined Galacta-Force instead to make a positive difference in the Galaxy and underwent exposure to Omni particles which gave her the ability of Laser Manipulation and Telepathy. Now she helps to keep the peace across the Galaxy as Lazer-Hawk. PERSONAL DATA Characteristics: Â· Species: Praxian Â· Age: 32 Â· Height: 5’11” Â· Weight: 124lbs Â· Eye Color: Violet Blue Â· Hair Color: Black (with luminescent strands) Â· Skin Color: Violet Status Â· Place of Birth: Praxis Â· Citizenship: Betrassus Â· Base: The Ixion Interceptor, Galactor Prime (Galactic Enforcer Headquarters) Â· Occupation: Space Explorer, Diplomat Â· Known Relatives: Mevtr Rannz(Father), Slexi Rannz(Mother), Kotva Ranzz(Older Brother, Deceased), Kryx tol Rannz(Older Brother), Ryruul(Little sister), Cozhana(Youngest sister), Ivtr Razz(Her C.O and FiancÃ©e, Deceased) . POWERS AND ABILITIES Power Grid Â· Intelligence: 4 Â· Strength: 4 Â· Speed: 7 Â· Durability: 3 Â· Energy Projection: 5 Â· Fighting Skills: 6 Laser Manipulation: Lazer-Hawk can create, shape and manipulate laser light, intense, coherent, monochromatic, parallel beam of light (infrared, visible, or ultraviolet) or other electromagnetic radiation, which is composed of waves of the same frequency and all in phase. Laser Attacks: she can create and project beams of laser that are capable of piercing virtually anything they come in contact with and have explosive properties Holographic Projection: she can create, shape and manipulate holograms, fully three-dimensional images of the holographed target Light speed: She is able to transform her body into living laser and can travel at the speed of light. Telepathy: She has the ability to mentally receive and transmit information. Enhanced Condition: Thanks to her genetic enhancements her body is at peak physical and mental condition which means that she is faster, stronger and smarter than anyone from her own race. Flight: Lazer-Hawk has the ability to fly and can perform interstellar space travel on her own Vacuum Adaptation: She has the ability to adapt to the vacuum of space unaided LIMITATIONS Â· May be unable to create laser, being limited to manipulating only from already existing sources. Â· She is limited to controlling lasers within a certain radius. Â· Her light attacks are ineffective against mirrored surfaces and may bounce off of them Â· She is vulnerable to Gravitational attacks SKILLS As a former member of the Alliance fleet she received advanced training in hand to hand and space combat. Thanks to her telepathic abilities she is Omni-lingual and is able to speak and understand any alien language fluently making her an expert in the art of diplomacy PARAPHERNALIA Her suit is specifically tailored to her power set and it is equipped with sufficient kinetic barriers to shield against energy and projectile based weaponry and can generate its own life support field when in deep space. The suit also comes with a protective navigation visor which she uses when in battle or making interstellar space travel PERSONALITY Ayala is more of a people person and has this ability to make someone feel good about his or herself. Though she is not very expressive in her behaviour she is a very sophisticated woman who has captivating charm and elegant taste. She has this nurturing personality about herself that draws people to her and will readily help a teammate or someone in need. She believes in diplomacy before violence but there are times where she may drop those ideals and do what must be done for the greater good. She is very intelligent and knows how to talk to people of different backgrounds. However she feels uncomfortable taking the role of a leader. But when the situation calls for it she will give it her all and lead her team to victory. She dreams of a peaceful Galaxy and will fight to make that dream a reality.

description: Lest we Canadians forget, it's been an absurdly warm fall. September in particular was brutally hot, and living in an air conditioned apartment meant that my brain was a little fried on more than one occasion. Claire is here to remind us how difficult it can be to cool down during a heat wave. Even with a full tank of water to cool her down, she just doesn't do well in sauna-like temperatures. With all that in mind, this approaching winter doesn't seem so bad! ...Ok, winter still sucks. Just enjoy the fanservice. Even Claire likes to show off every once in a while~ To address the title, while Claire's specific species isn't known, she is a sort of amphibian-mammal hybrid, somewhere between Axi and Ignis. So, let's call her a salamander for now. Don't worry, she's not slimy, just a little sweaty at the moment~ Claire is (c) Me

description: Aaaaaand finally!! A new post! This week was terrible, computer crashed, didnÂ´t save the day after that, they cut the electricity, didnÂ´t save. Lost my progress twice. The mantra for this week is save often!!!! IÂ´m on a fairy row!! A very possible scenario. There are lots of spider peril pics out there. This idea has been circling my thoughts for a long time. I wanted to portray the sense of terror and helplessness that must be crossing tinkerbellÂ´s mind while being captured by a monstrous garden spider. I searched the web for inspiration trying to find the perfect perspective and depth to communicate the use Mr. Smith voice- inevitability of tinkÂ´s fate. The inspiration came from the pic arachnophobia by gamera 1985. Go check it. Imagine the precise moment she crashes into the web, an instant of WTF, followed by a gasp, shortness of breath upon realizing where she is, oh no , oh no, oh no, oh no, oh no, no please no, she thinks-, heart racing at 200 per minute, she looks at the web strings, so thin and silky, so sticky, yet so resistant. She tries to break free. With each movement she gets ensnared more and more in the sticky threads . Each struggle signaling through vibrations that dinner is ready. The spider is the perfect bondage predator created by nature, cold and inexpressive, in a split second it falls over its prey, surrounding her, no escape, no use for screaming. First disabling the means of escape to secure the catch, some web strings around the wings, arms and legs, fighting becomes a very futile struggle with each web spun around her. Wings stop fluttering, Her movement reduced to a grub-like motion. The final struggles will be dealed with in no time, a small bite, some neurotoxin waiting until it kicks in, watching how her strength abandons her, how she loses control of her body, how her muscles gradually cease responding,  The wonderful thing about web is its design by nature: thin but very resistant. I took research seriously and read some articles about spiderweb. I tried to portray web strings as a silky-thin-traslucid thread, not as a gooey thick blob that is usually drawn like. It also took some research time with layers and filters to get that effect. Hope it was worth it. I hope the spider is scary enough. Very satisfied with the background, wanted to transmit the sensation that the forest was helping the spider to catch tinkerbell, and if the spider failed, the forest would finish the job. ...Next time IÂ´ll use bigger leaves to show accurate scale. Used some tree and leaves brushes that I found on DA.Credit to The original title was "Fairies canÂ´t scream" since in the original movie, tinkerbell was mute. Then I remembered about the new tinkerbell series where she talks, so goodbye title. Couldnt think of a better one. Any suggestions? Does anyone reads this?

description: Edit: I wasn't happy with the fire, so I played with some layer settings to make it more luminescent and transparent. Very glad you can see her other eye now. I also made the sig more pronounced and made a few touch-ups here and there. Here to celebrate my 100th deviation we have the Blackâ˜…Rock Shooter, who despite not really being a vocaloid has indeed been exposed to the office-catgirl-ification. First of all I should point out that this was a commission from *Kelanich, so if you like this and are feeling amiable, go thank him! Now prepare for a rant: I don't like to brag, but I think this is the best thing I've drawn to date. I say this knowing full and well that I will never produce something this good ever again, unless by some miracle I find a way to simplify my shading process. Blending in Photoshop using only the brush takes an enormous amount of time/patience/sanity. As of now I only have one of those things remaining... So yeah, probably my best contribution to the Nekoloid series. IA won't be nearly this detailed, as I think I'm going to return to the flat colored and sketchy style that I've been developing. I feel those drawing are more lively. Getting this done is basically quite a load off my chest. I hope you all like it, especially you Kel. Other Nekoloids: ----------------------- For the After *Shattered-Earth did a correction for my shading on one of my other nekoloids, I tried to keep her advice in mind as much as possible. However since I'm not a perfect student by any means, I most definitely have messed up somewhere. Please help me with shading! Blackâ˜…Rock Shooter Â© Huke Drawing Â© Myself

description: Most people, who follow my art know I love mecha. But in that category I have a special spot for jets, specifically fighter jets! description: If the huns had won.... I still donÂ´t get a hold on pen tool lineart. Still, I depicted mulan with a flowing, delicate lineart, like that of a calligraphy brush, with attention to line quality. On the other hand, ropes are straight and cold. Shan yu started as a pen tool lineart practice, but got bored and finished him freehand. Shan yu is evil. Disney character designers are geniuses. They managed to portray a very evil character that takes over you. I mean when you try to draw him, even if you are a beginner, you cannot draw him funny or goofy, you feel the weight on every line, each color was chosen to strike fear, and those reverse colored eyes, its like an alien that stares into my soul Added green lingerie as a final touch, kind of emulating a jade ornament (also the picture had no green on it, so now mulan stands out.) First time I use a double light source -suggested by the chinese lamp from the ceiling- because mulan was too dark with only the light from the window. Tried to stay true to chinese decoration; it is easy to confuse japanese and chinese culture at some details. I was going for a shibari style, but i like some simmetry on the ropes. Besides shibari is a japanese bondage art form. Mulan and shan yu property of disney. art by me.

description: If there's a better title you want for this pic, Gold, tell me! Bzzt. *taps microphone* Is this thing on? Once again, I disappear for months and return with something reasonably...large. Like this thing that I've been working on for eons, which is responsible for both killing and revitalizing my inspiration for art. Not at the same time. BASICALLY... It's half a trade, half a commission, with who else but GoldenGriffiness! And a very big trade/commission at that. If you're unaware of Goldy's 'Legend of Cynder' fanfiction series...clearly you haven't been watching me for very long, because I've done a fair bit of art for it. Buuuut, whatever the case, here's a link: www.fanfiction.net/s/6782003/1… This particularly artwork refers to the third installment of the series, which follows the DotD timeline...and has yet to be written. Get on with it, Gold! On the left there is Travix the blood dragon, brainchild of Dardarax, who lent him to Goldy to undergo unfathomable changes to his design and character. On the right, Viriti and Myst, and Kaboa the spirit dragoness looming over everyone in the back, all Goldy's characters. And if you don't know Spyro, Cynder and Sparx, what are you doing here? And I don't know what else to say, because I've been working on this piece for so long that my brain is all confuzzled now that it's done. Send help. This thing is massive. Downloading recommended. Unless you have a terrible internet connection. Almost forgot, here's the background on its own, since so much of it is covered: sta.sh/01x7dj1wii0x

description: The Lost Squire Ever since I read the story of Pyra in 's interview with Jared Pullen , I've been fascinated with the idea of this little guy. Whether or not his story is canon, I still love the concept of Ignitus's battlesquire who got lost in the War. I thought it would be nice to make him share some features with Spyro, since Ignitus was supposedly very fond of Pyra, he would then carry that fondness onto little Spyro when they first meet. And it's also because I think Spyro looks as if he has some Fire Dragon physical traits. I don't know I just wanted to draw him.

description: My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic - Cake Monster This is something of a landmark comic for me. It's the first MLP strip that I've done where I haven't simply copied\pasted other people's ponies in, or used a Pony Generator. Pretty much everything in this strip was created in either scratch drawn in Photoshop or Inkscape (My first Inkscape strip, yay) using images from the show, or other source material. Frame 1 Most of Frame 1 was scratch built in Photoshop or Inkscape. I used sircinnamon's Celestia ([link]) and McAwesomeBrony's Celestia ([link]) as a base for my own model. As well as a couple of different shots from the show. I imagine this is how Celestia would look as a teenager. She has pink hair as that's the color that is was show in the introduction to series one. I couldn't get the detail right on the crown or the necklace, so I put hearts in instead. I figure that she might have worn a different style when she was younger. I've also drawn her wings differently. They are much more pert than in the series. Kinda like when you're a teenager and you buy your first pushup bra, and it makes you've got Kim Possible boobs. Her Cutie Mark is from ooklah ([link]), as I saw no reason to go over old ground again. Frame 2 Frame 2 is pretty much like frame 1. Everything is either scratch built in Photoshop or Inkscape. Same base's Princess Celestia. Frame 3 Frame 3 is a based on Frame 2. I use transparencies and fill effects on her tail and mane in Inkscape to make it look like she's really angry then I exported it to Photoshop where I added the shadow, and tinted her colors to make it look like she's glowing with rage. I deliberately made her feathers spiky rather than smooth as in the show to show how angry she is. She's literately bristling with rage. I'd have liked to have the refrigerator melting away or the floor tiles cracking, maybe I will update it to include these things sometime. Maybe not. I guess that's what differentiates hobbyist like me from real artists. Princess Luna was drawn in Inkscape using images from the show as a base. I'm not particularly happy with the eyes or the mouth and may re-draw them some time. The eye was meant to look catlike, but it didn't come out so good, and the teeth are too small. Frame 4 I must admit here that the background from Frame 4 isn't my doing. It was drawn by theirishbronyx ([link]). The Moon Canon and Princess Luna were both drawn in Inkscape. Frame 5 See Frame 1 and 4.

description: As far as Cassidy knows, it's been a lazy day of doing nothing while his sister is out of town on errands, and he was just peacefully napping for the night. He seriously doesn't recall having murdered anyone! Fun Facts: Most wolves do not divulge their last names to any but family, especially during the five years that they must remain without contact from their parents. They must prove their strength and find their 'pack' (relationships) outside of their family before returning. The majority of pack rituals are no longer practiced since it was believed the wolves evolved to the intelligent state they are in today. Wolves and Canines in this story age slower than humans in our world (and humans do not exist). A 50 year old wolf would be around age 42 for us. She loves scrapers in the back and neck. She likes to chase small animals for fun. She loves people who do not claim to change what she is and people who love having their own space and leave those her as well. She does not like people jealous and possessive. She is truly faithful only to those who treats her with respect.

description: I needed to make a poster with Moon Dancer since I role play her a lot. Additionally I wanted to have a trilogy so here's the first part. Since Moon Dancer has two different mane styles in the show, I decided to do at least one picture with both manes. Bonus content for part1: Twilights mane Background story: Part 1: After searching another week through all the books in the Royal Nightmare Library Moon Dancer is confident that she found the right selection of books for the mighty ruler of the night. Now she can face her majesty Nightmare Moon without fear. Every single little doubt disappeared as she reminded herself that she knew all books perfectly well. She cannot just present any selection, it must be perfect. And this is what she has done. Part 2: As we know every ruler need subjects to command at. That's also true for our dark mare of the moon. At this night she ordered Moon Dancer to bring her good books for her entertainment. Tragicly there is a missmatch between Moon Dancer and the royal pony of the night. Full of anger the mighy started to shout at Moon Dancer. >Who do you think am I? "Advanced Astronomy"?. I am the queen of the night and I know every star on the firmament.< Moon Dancer wanted to respond with a clear mind but the dark pony just didn't stopped to use her Royal Canterlot Voice. Hours later our pale student was dismissed to leave the room without any words spoken. Part 3: The only cure for that terrible feeling would be a lonely place to cry everything out loudly. Fortunately she knows the castle perfectly well and where to go next. Nopony shall know that Nightmare Moon rejected her again. But unfortunately she only can hope that the next visit will be less depressing. Credits Nightmare Castle by Nightmare Moon by ENH NMM by Moon Dancer by ENH Moon Dancer by Openable Books by Books from FS cottage by MLP:Fim by Hasbro

description: Too tired... Hey look! I did a thing with the thing! Yes...it's been awhile since I've done a line-art piece, but I made it out alive! So I think I'll be adding this option to commissions for you guys that are more leaning on line-art. I'd prefer my style any day, but I will always be happy to try new things and improving. That said, this is available as a print! Yay! So here you guys go! I searched awhile to try and find a Fluttercord piece that was "epic" that had come from the episode "Make New Friends But Keep Discord" episode...but surprisingly I hadn't found any yet...weird. So I thought I'd do something for the episode...even though it's been ages since its aired. (timing) Hope y'all enjoy! P.S. I got an editor for my fan-fics now! Yay! With Love, Lola

description: This was one of the ideas I've been wanting to do ever since I read the FanFiction, Equestrian Ninjas, At the end of Chapter 13, after Spike have transformed into a massive mutant, Wolfatizer and feld into the city. Last seen on Coney Island when April help Spike regain his conscious and is reunited with his friends. I even add some things to spice up the moment Reading the bubble diagram words from Spike to Twilight (Top Right To Bottom Right) Spike: It's good to see you Twilight, and all the rest of you. Princess Twilight: Oh Spike....(Sniff Sniff) I was afraid I lost you forever....(sobbing) I can't tell where I be without you. Spike: You can't keep a dog or dragon down Twi. Princess Twilight: (Giggles)..(Sniff)... Spike: There now. You need to get yourself together. I'm here now. Come on, dry up those tears Princess Twilight Sparkle (MLP EG 2013) Spike (MLP EG 2013) Credit of the FanFiction goes to DarkMagicianmon Source for the Idea goes to jebens1

description: An ultimate crossover between four of my favorite franchises. Imagine four groups coming together by fate to fight off the ultimate of all evil, Master Xehanort and the two very threats of all worlds scattered, the Heartless and Nobodies. They all travel from world to world, fighting, sealing the keyholes, opening new paths, and bringing peace to all. First one is their original forms as they travel to worlds at least two times (Destiny Islands, Wonderland, Deep Jungle, Olympus Coliseum, Agrabah, Monstro, Neverland, Radiant Garden (Hollow Baston), Twilight Town, Land Of Dragons, Beast's Castle, Disney Castle, Port Royal, New York City, Canterlot High, End of the World (Heartless World), World That Never Was (Nobody World), Castle Oblivion, etc.) Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Leonardo (Leo) (Leader) (Katana Swords) Raphael (Raph) (Brute Muscle) (Sai Daggers) Donatello (Donnie) (Brains) (Bo Staff) Michelangelo (Mikey) (Party Dude) (Nunchucks) My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Twilight Sparkle (Leader/Brains Girl) (Kamayari Sickle Spear) Sunset Shimmer (Leader Girl) (Kunai Daggers With Pouch) Applejack (Brute Muscle Girl) (Shuko Hand Claws) Fluttershy (Kind Girl) (Fukedake Blowgun, Darts, and Pouch) Pinkie Pie (Party Girl) (Bakuhatsugama Sickle and Weight Chain) Rarity (Fashion Girl) (Kama Sickles) Rainbow Dash (Brute Force/Awesome Girl) (Naginita Spear) Sly Cooper Gang: Sly Cooper (Master Thief/Leader) (Cooper Cane) Bentley (Brains) (Mechanical Wheelchair with Accessories and Gadgets) Murray (Muscle) (Boxing Gloves) Carmelita (Law/Brute Force) (Shock Pistol) Dimitri Lousteau (Party/Disco/Scuba Diver Dude) (Lousteau Cane) Kingdom Hearts Warriors: Sora (Leader) (Keyblade) Donald (Court Magician/Brains) (Magi Staff) Goofy (Court Knight/Heart) (Knight Shield) Note: Ive been wanting to do this for such a long time when seeing all four of the major franchises to this day. This is one of the nine pieces that I will be doing for a long while. EG Ninja Weapons designed by yours truly, BozzerKazooers from the Fanfiction Equestria Ninjas by DarkMagicianmon TMNT 2012-Present by Nickelodeon MLP EG 2013-Present by Hasbro and Discovery Family Sly Cooper Games 2002-Present by Sucker Punch and Sanzaru Games Kingdom Hearts 2002-Present by Disney and Square Index Games

description: Now this is yet another fantastic design scene layout idea that I imagine, since the night I have seen special premiere of MLP Movie. In this scene, the confrontation commenced where I had TMNT 2012 Leonardo clashing with the Storm King, just as he was about to whip out Princess Twilight and Tempest Shadow. I even thought of how this could word out: Just a the Storm King was about to vaporize Twilight and Tempest, a shrunken star landed on Storm Kings back armor. Storm King- WHAT?!? Who dares strike the Storm King?!? Voice- I did baboon face! The three turned around as Leo stepped out of the Shadows. Princess Twilight- Leo! You came! Tempest- I dont believe it. Storm King- What is this?!? More Hybrid Ponies?!? I thought Blade Swipe was the only of his kind. Leo- Yeah and this kind of hybrid pony that's gonna put an end to your rain of terror parade banana breath! Storm King- You will try Then the two go at each other, until reinforcements arrived from thin air Pretty good huh? Credit of the FanFiction goes to DarkMagicianmon

description: <notice> you can be cameo. please join me. <Update and Silrent Dash's comment> -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Ok, I'm the guy who translates it from Korean to English, and I've just noticed something was off with the translation. First of all, I apologize with all the confusion on page 80 (and perhaps making this comic much less interesting). I misread and misunderstood what GashibokA has written, so I ended up translating it incorrectly, turning it into a different story. So it is suppose to be Empress Twilight was worrying about that Crimson Changelings have infiltrated the pony society. So ponies who were accused of being a Crimson Changeling were all captured. (That's why there's the posters) But then Twilight was arresting too many ponies without any solid evidence or whatsoever, so ponies who were against this has formed Resistance against Twilight. I already talked to GashibokA, and he will fix it soon. And there are no major error in translation in previous pages, so don't worry too much about being mislead. Once again, I truly apologizing for almost ruining this amazing story of GashibokA. I'll review my translation and make sure it's quite accurate. I hope you all can enjoy reading this great comic until the end. -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- If you want hear about this comic's news immediately, follow this twitter account. description: I had some spare time over Thanksgiving break so i decided to do a star wars piece since I havent done anything star wars in years. I dig mmo's (even though I dont have time to play them at the moment) so I decided to do a sort of pin up/ cover type image and color it to stay sharp with my coloring. I chose to do one of the classes in the game called the Sith Juggernaut as it was the most interesting to me. This was colored with pscs3 over my pencils and I swiped the logos from the interwebs and messed with them some. This might end up in my portfolio if I can get a good print, I'd love to do some covers or comics for darkhorse/ starwars Star Wars belongs to lucasarts and etc yadda yadda yadda, I dont own star wars so on and so forth. Enjoy! The guys at swtor liked this pic and put it up on thier fan friday [link]

description: This is an important piece of art to me. It's so far outside of what I usually do, and I didn't think I could do it. I've been in such a bad place lately, getting jealous of my friends and angry at myself and feeling conflicted about my own art. But the other day I felt a moment of clarity and I thought about things and really turned a corner. I decided I was not going to let my demons beat me! I was going to try! so I put aside my stubbornness and went home and decided I was going to try! and try I did, and this picture is the result! proof that I can be anything I want to be. And made Pinkie Pie taking a nice autumn walk. description: And another ode to classic pinups of years gone past, Chad had posted this one not too long ago here. Chad had been toying around for poses, and I mentioned something about swiping a few ideas from Vargas and Elvgren. Little did I know that he would actually take me seriously! So, here's my attempt at trying to complete the illusion of a 50s type pinup piece, but with Detresse flair. I did not shine up her top as I usually do, hoping it would give a more retro vibe to the piece. Unlike the previous piece, I used a dark brown for the black parts. I hope you enjoy. Lines: Chad Heinrich =cheinrich1981 Colours: me =jwwebb I want to say thank ahead of time for those ing this deviation. I'd like to individually thank you all but it has really become time consuming... But because of your support, you not only help the ego but also help let me know that I must be doing something right. Thank you!

description: In response to hundreds of requests! - okay, one reader asked for this, but I'm sure there are hundreds who were thinking about asking for it! - I've produced a version of Sonya 30-day OC Challenge - Day 30 without Tetsuko, so you can get a better look at Sonya's rather spectacularly-peaked bicep. One of many reasons why I enjoy working digitally is that reworking a piece like this is relatively easy, compared to analog art. I simply lasso the portions of the art that I want to remove, hit "delete", use the eraser tool to fine-tune the deletion, and add color to the portions covered by Tetsuko's fingers. I also edited Sonya's eyes so that she's looking at you (with that smile that seems to ask "you like what you see?"), and added a new background. Doing all this with real-world materials would have involved redrawing or retracing the art, which would've involved hours of work - and color? Fuggeddaboudit! I couldn't work in color if not for software like SmithMicro's Manga Studio EX 5, or Adobe Photoshop (although I'm using MS5EX for about 99.5% of my work these days). And I added a little "glow" around Sonya's bicep because, well, I just like the effect!

description: GAYAS ORIGIN Gayas is a Thaessian born on the planet Ekos whose race are able to transform their bodies completely into the fundamental elements of air, earth, water, fire, electricity, light and shadow. When her planet was under attack by a Mutilon Invasion, The Galacta-Force intervened and helped her people to defeat them. Impressed by her fighting capabilities Galacta-Force asked her to join their organization which she accepted very willingly. PERSONAL DATA Characteristics: Â· Species: Thaesssian (Humanoid) Â· Age: 131 Â· Height: 6’5” Â· Weight: 206lbs Â· Eye Color: Cyan Â· Hair Color: Yellowish Green Â· Skin Color: Pale Yellow Status Â· Place of Birth: Ekos Â· Citizenship: None Â· Rank: Sub Enforcer Â· Base: Ixion Interceptor, Galactor Prime (Galacta-Force Headquarters) Â· Occupation: Adventurer Â· Known Relatives: Rokk (Father), Yura Val (Mother), Gazi Mo (Younger Brother), Teraki (Grandmother), Vero (Uncle) POWERS AND ABILITIES Power Grid Â· Intelligence: 3 Â· Strength: 6 Â· Speed: 2 Â· Durability: 7 Â· Energy Projection: 3 Â· Fighting Skills: 6 Elemental Mimicry: she has the ability to transform her body completely into the fundamental elements of air, earth, electricity, fire, light, shadow and water. She can transform into homogenous matter, without any part of her form being more important than the other. Elemental Shapeshifting: She can transform/reshape her form to enhance her body for combat using some surrounding elements. Enhanced Stamina: Her Thaessian physiology allows her to function for long periods of time without tiring or straining herself. Enhanced Durability: In her earth form her body is extremely durable making her almost immune to physical attack. Enhanced Strength: her strength is increased tenfold when she is in her earth form and is able to lift over 30tons easily. Enhanced Agility: she has the ability to go from one motion to another effortlessly, effectively dodge attacks, swing from things easily, sprint, do back-flips and numerous other gymnastic, athletic and martial implements with little effort. Oxygen Independence: Gayas has no need for oxygen, allowing her to survive indefinitely in airless environments. LIMITATIONS Â· She can only mimic substances she can touch Â· She can only transform into one element at a time, and she must first return back to her normal form before changing to another element. Â· Her abilities are greatly limited when in a vacuum such as deep space. SKILLS Thanks to her upbringing she has total mastery of her abilities and is able to defend herself in hand to hand combat. She is also able to perceive the terrain of her immediate surroundings on any planet she is on, making her an excellent Navigator. PARAPHERNALIA Her suit is composed of smart molecules which changes into the exact atomic structure her body mimics into along with kinetic barriers to shield against energy and projectile based weaponry and can generate its own life support field when in deep space. PERSONALITY Gayas has a very vibrant, expansive personality that is free like a bird. She is very positive and optimistic in any situation. She is spontaneous and adventurous and loves to be were the action is. Despite her spontaneous personality she is very smart and is capable of understanding complex things. She relates well with others and is well liked because of her encouraging positive nature and her kind heart. But there are times when she can be reckless and irresponsible because she will jump immediately into battle without a battle plan or strategy or fail to follow orders and protocol. She gets incredibly bored with so much formality but tries her best to make herself a useful team player. She has a deep desire to explore the vast reaches of space, go on exciting and thrilling adventures and do her best to make the Universe a safer place for all life.

description: EDIT YouTube (speedpaint) link here. Here...have some fluttercord! Texas needs rain...like, now T-T I can't take the heat any longer...colder weather is needed... Don't ask why I'm doing fall art when I should be enjoying summer...I honestly like colder weather, but that's just me. I think I'm getting WAY better now, and I have found my style ^w^ I'll admit practice is all I need, but I think I'm getting there and my style of painting has really grown. _____________ Hey look critique! If you want to add a critique, please, name off the flaws...I can take it. A good critique both compliments and points out fixable flaws. I'd appreciate it if, you as a critic, would tell me what in general should be fixed or polished off to be better. I do love compliments, but I also love opinions too. Also, understand that this is my style so it isn't like others, so I can't be exactly like someone else. Just tell me what you think would look better or that I should work on. ______________________ Inspired by this, by the way~ Speedpaint Video will be updated on here soon...and my page I think ^^ Hope you enjoy this! With Love, Lola

description: Now this is yet another fantastic design scene layout idea that I imagine, since the night I have seen special premiere of MLP Movie. In this scene, as the group received news of Twilight's capture by Tempest Shadow and that Leo going after them, the group had to figure how to help their friends, until a familiar face came along. Capper as he leap down to the group- Well good thing I know a group that can handle the situation easily Raph- YOU?!?! Raph charged at him, grabbed his coat and pinned him against the boulder Rarity walked up- Well look what the cat dragged in? Himself!! Capper- Now now I know things did not really go as I plan due to me getting carried away by my little itch of habit... Raph- Funny, the only thing Im gonna be carrying away is another one of your nine lives puss in boots!! Capper- Wait, before you punch my lights out, just hear what I have to say. I may have a proposition that can save us from this Stormy mess. Sunset- Hold on Raph, even though he betrayed us, I think we should hear what he has to say Raph groaned- Alright.....you got a minute fur ball. Better make it quick. description: If people been following the character building process- Eagle's OLD design was Native American- but due to some origin story timeline issues, we had to completely change and re-write her origin-thus change her whole character concept. To Aztec- But as soon as we did, everything fell into place, her look, her tattoo, her outfits, and even her dragon- the Quetzalcoatl. Quetza as she is called as the Orsian God of Wind. Eagle's true name is Izel, but nicknamed Eagle, for her incredible eyesight, her powers that make her almost fly, and the ginormous eagle tattoo covering her chest. Eagle's personality however, has not changed one bit. She's one of the less serious characters, brings a heavy dose of comedy in the story along with a few other characters. Playing mind games, pranks on both friend and foe and loves to jump into battle with the bad puns and one-liners. She's a tormentor within the group, pranks in the variety on her favorite targets: Silver and Nola. ( She does prank the others, but they deliver weak reactions compared to those two. However, she does not prank Cerridwen, for obvious reasons, and Kat- She has tried to, but Kat somehow knows every time) And because of her pranking nature, she has the most 'trollish' face when she's up to no good. I honestly won't be surprised if she becomes and Icon for it... Beyond the fun and games, Eagle's a very well established fighter. She's extremely light on her feet (the woman can squat) balancing on her toes and balls of her feet. Manipulating the force and velocity of wind can make her nearly soundless and weightless to her foes, but when directing her powers upon her enemies, that same weightless air can switch into gale force winds tossing her foes high in the air ( or tossing them through concrete) to deadly torrential/ hurricane force. What aids her in her battle is her Bladed 'Tonfans'. I spent days agonizing how these would look and thanks to my partner in crime and Editor, we were able to create these badboys. Painted in the colors of the Quetzalcoatl, and the carved head of the Quetzalcoatl on the end. Eagle's changes has made me come to absolutely LOVE the use of Aztec colors and designs, and... I really want her pants... Working on her expression sheet next. Troll face will be included. It's nice to finally achieve something after a full 4 day drawing block. Eagle Â©2013 THE ELEMENTS. All rights reserved

description: Comic made of playing cards~ I altered the joker's poses in the computer, printed them, and then cut them all out with tiny scissors. Besides the two jokers, the rest of the cards are from the actual deck. I painted over parts of them, drew on them, "aged" the edges with brown ink, and glued the speech bubbles on top. The background is acrylic paint. Photo is the best I could get--this thing is HUUGE. Poor joker...but it's okay, we all know he isn't the real fool.

description: Here's my commission of 's Original Character Sonya 'Archangel' Blade. This is the 4th time I've drawn Sonya and this time ReddofNonnac trusted me with the markers. I've been really getting into the marker drawings lately, just don't get enough damn time to do more! (I know, I know - I'm bitching about not having any time again) The brief was to do a cheesecake pin-up of her showing off her impossible strength... in a bikiini. I won't lie, I really struggled with this to start with. I had a tough time coming up with an idea that was sexy and impossibly strong whilst keeping it convincing. I'm also a bit of a nightmare in the sense that I like to have a bit of exposition for a pic, so in my head I was thinking, "How do I explain a giantess working out in a bikini using something that shows how incredibly strong she is?" But then I remembered that not many pin-ups need explaining! There's not many photos of women in bikinis from a studio shoot that have an elaborate back story so after I realised I was being daft I eventually got round to coming up with something decent! Those of you in the know will probably recognise the pose. I found a pic of 90's fbb Denise Rutkowski and thought that it would make an awesome pin-up with a little bit of tweaking. I swapped the dumbbell for a wrecking ball, adjusted the figure a little here and there and replaced her head with Sonya's. This pic was done on 350gsm card using Warm and Cool Grey Copic markers, Pigma Micron and Pitt Pens, White Gel pen and black and white pencil crayon. The copics and the pencils give a very nice soft look to the art but drawing and shading muscle is pretty damn time consuming! Check out 's page for more artwork and info on Sonya!

description: Another Crossover Project that features two of my favorite tv franchises. Involves another time for the Rainbooms and their Pets to come together for pictures for Animal Calendar. They convinced the Turtles and Human Allies to bring forth their own pets to share this tradition. This is 1 of 4 Designs Leonardo (TMNT 2012) and his new pet Akita Dog, Yoshi (TMNT 2012) Twilight Sparkle (MLP EG 2015) and her companion, Spike The Dog (MLP EG 2015) Karai Hamato (TMNT 2012) with her new pet snake, Shen (TMNT 2013) Note: The Akita Dog and The Snake are really confirmed from the TMNT 2012, but anything could happen in the Equestria Ninja Fic World The Akita Dog, Hachiko was former pet dog belonging to the Shredder. But after Shredder was slain, the dog fend for himself, out in the streets searching for food and shelter. It wasn't very long until he was discovered by April and Casey whom somehow show compassion to the dog and then had an idea. They know that the three turtles, Raph, Donnie and Mikey have their own pets, either mutant or alien, it would seem fitting that Leo should have his own pet. Thus entering the Akita Dog. It did not take long for the dog to have his loyalty/allegiance change to Leo, for the two share a common bond, fighting for honor and peace. And it did not take Leo to figure a name for the dog, none other than his Master/Father (Hamato Yoshi). There fore Yoshi is the name for the Akita Dog. The two are in sync. The Snake was one of the other snakes that were in the cage from Shredder's plan to use Karai as bait to lure Splinter and the Turtles from hiding, have them captured and turn them into mindless snake mutants. Unfortunetly the plan backfired and end up turning Karai into her Snake Mutant. When the area was caught on fire, the Snakes have escaped and fled somewhere in the city. Eventually the one snake had slithered to Former Shredder's hideout, now belonging to Karai as she restores order to the Foot Ninja Clan. Karai discovered this lonesome snake and senses, the snake is a she and is very lonesome. It was long before Karai decided to take her in and consider her a pet. The name she has chosen was from her dear dead mother, Tang Shen. There fore Shen became suited for the Snake. Like Leo and his Pet, the two were in sync. Now the three pets are getting along well together, as their owners embrace this moment Request By Pokemon4845 Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (2012-Present) My Little Pony Equestria Girls (2013-Present)

description: I'VE DONE IT!!! The very piece I have been wanting to do for bout a year but could not find the time to do so until now. Just another romantic theme for TMNT Leonardo and MLP FIM and EG Twilight Sparkle (Both Counterparts) as they embrace the Holiday Cheer. One time as the Ninja Group and Rainbooms start to celebrate Christmas, Leo and Twilight were caught under the Mistletoe. Both were nervous in the kissing part but they went a did it. Added bubbles to spice up the moment Leo on thought: Come on Leo! Go for it! What are you afraid of? Twilight in thought: Maybe I should make the first move (giggle) KISSING Leo in thought: Ok...that was worth the wait Twilight: Merry Christmas Leo Leo: Merry Christmas Twilight Another time when the Ninja Group went back to Equestria with Sunset to visit Princess Twilight and her friends as they were setting up for Hearts Warming. As all were enjoying themselves, once again Leo and Princess Twilight were caught under the Mistletoe and embrace the moment. Leo in thought: Turtle up dude and kiss her! Princess Twilight in thought: I can see he is about as nervous as I am KISSING (With song playing from Samurai Jack Season 5 as Jack and Ashi kissed) Princess Twilight: Happy Hearts Warming Leo Leo: Happy Hearts Warming Twilight Note: This is my final design piece til we hit 2018. I would like to enjoy the rest of the Christmas month and New Years Eve-Day. So let me say, Merry Christmas!! And A Happy New Year to all!! Leonardo (TMNT 2012) Twilight Sparkle (MLP EG 2015) (New Outfit 2017) Princess Twilight (MLP FIM 2011-Present)

It depicts a feisty red-head called Dawn Keenan who hunts vampires in Dublin.
