description: After 3 weeks of no art at all I had some trouble getting back in the painting groove. Especially since I didn't have my normal painting program so which meant I had to use photoshop x3 Which didn't go well. Luckily I found a way to get sai in my hands after all. Did some warm up sketches and decided to go make a full drawing out of the flutter sketch I had. it was gonna be just flutterbutt at first but then I thought, why not try something new. Make a background x3 I really hope it looks okay enough for it to be on here. I honestly think it needs a lot of work buts it's also pretty good for a first try at a more detailed background. oh.. oh dear... my coat is getting all wet... ----------- Program used: Paint Tool Sai Time: 25 ish hours, working slow but gud <3 Horseness belongs to Hasbro Art by ----------- Commissions are open! fav.me/dacu0uw Wanna see me livestream? Come and join me in Picarto! picarto.tv/Pucksterv Happy fluttery horse Horsing

Did some warm up sketches and decided to go make a full drawing out of the flutter sketch I had. it was gonna be just flutterbutt at first but then I thought, why not try something new. Said she got the sword in some place called Melnibone, back when that sorta thing was in...You know girls and their ancient runeswords...pfft... description: A HUGE JACK POSTER!!! <3 I worked for like...a week on this! :'D And finally...it;s done! <3 And I just wanna say something: I want to thank you all for reading and supporting my story. Since the first time I came here, I thought that I won't become noticed. But thanks to my Jack comic and lovely comments of all my fans and friends...I was able to to continue it. I've putted all my heart and soul in this story. Humor, sadness, love, happyness, anger and creativity. I'm proud to say that I finally finished this. There have been times that I thought...Iquit. But then, I remembered...why I am doing this. Why I'm making this. I'm trying to safe the sharks. But when you're trying to safe sharks, you're trying to safe all of us. Like Susan the blacktip reef shark said in the comic, we can't live without sharks. They keep the ocean in balance. And if not, then we would die too. With this story, I want to make people laugh, cry and let them realize what we're doing. What we're doing wrong and how we can solve it. How we can protect the ocean. And how to love sharks. But Jack's journey is not over. The sharks journey, is never over. The shark has been here, for 450 million years...I want them to keep moving. I want them to keep us alive. Sharks will always be...ontop. Thank you for reading this. Enjoy! Jack theblack shark ( c ) laura Zavraan After this story, spin offs who don't officialy count as sequals will be made.

description: Another commission done by my favorite artist, MugenIllustrations I do not own Marvel's Peter Parker (Spider-Man) or Hasbro's Twilight Sparkle and Princess Luna. No question this is one of my favorite commissions. 'Spiders and Magic: Rise of Spider-Mane' has gone through several title pictures. This is another, although I want to keep this one around as long as possible. You all already know of my love for the pairing of ParkerxSparkle, but where does my love for Luna stand? Pretty high up, really. She's my third favorite character in Friendship is Magic behind Fluttershy and Twilight Sparkle. In Spiders and Magic, it's hinted that she's enamored with Peter, but where do her feelings really stand? Read the links below to find out. If you're not interested, it's fine. description: Cupcakes & Baloons This is an interpretive picture based on the style of DShou, a lovely artist I have been a fan of for awhile! Deviantart â—? Tumblr What that means is I basically tried to make a picture mimicing the artist's style so I could try it out and get a feel for it. This is good for multiple things; I can learn new things, it shows my appreciation forthe artist, helps spread their exposure, and if they see it, they just might pick up some ideas too! I felt like trying out the style they use since it’s so cute~ And I may try this with other artists in the future too. it’s a fantastic learning experience and it’s always good to try new things. I love how he does eyes, so cute~ Although the mane & tail were kind of an experiment by me. shading and highlights included. So everypony should go check out the rest of his gorgeous art, if you know what’s good for you! hehe. Also, here’s a version with my style colour overlays and backgroundless version Two freebies in a row what is wrong with me XD
